result.reviews.text: If you're stuck in the building doing jury duty and you just want to order a coffee and eat the lunch you brought, you're out of luck. Never mind that half the tables are empty -- you will be asked to leave, because there's no outside food allowed and rules are rules.

result.adr_address: 555 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.formatted_address: 555 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Fine & Rare

result.reviews.text:
This space has gone through many changes over the years.  I hope Fine & Rare sticks around.

I ordered their rotisserie turkey salad.  And for $12 it can feed 2 people.  It is a huge portion of greens, moist turkey, and fresh avocado.  I also ordered a side of caramelized brussels sprouts.  The brussels sprouts was plenty of food already as I finished that and couldn't finish the rest of my salad.  The sprouts were roasted perfectly and had a good balance of sweet and savory.

The space is very clean and small.  The turnaround time is pretty quick though.  The menu isn't extensive so it won't take long for you to order.  I also like that each item has a sandwich or salad option.  Even if you do get the sandwich, it comes with a generous side salad.

I'm so happy for this new, healthy addition at Civic Center.

Went to an event here where we rented out the entire space and had beer & wine and appetizers. 

The red wine selected was definitely strange, the bartender explained it to me, but ultimately it just tasted sour. It was bottled as you'd expect a hipster to package wine. For my next two drinks, I selected the white wine (much better), and a beer that I can't recall, but it was a premium selection.

The appetizers were substantial and were enough to make a dinner out of. There were several types of bruschetta, which were just ok. A little hard, and hard to eat as well - the toppings came tumbling off. Normally, that's okay. But when you're standing and eating, it needs to be easier to eat. The sliders were very good. I loved the vegetarian one, spinach and mushroom and cheese. The BBQ chicken one was also quite good.

I'd recommend this place for a small event. The staff were friendly, and keep the food coming out until the very end!
Relaxing environment, jazzy music, delicious offerings, friendly staff.
The bone broth is amazing, and it isnt served everyday so when I see they have it, its a treat. The salads are generous and really great. Nice casual atmosphere, and ingredients fresh
Good chicken sandwich and GREAT french fries. Casual, counter serve place with a respectable beer selection and modern interior. Friendly and helpful staff.

result.reviews.text: Diner style food. It's a somewhat drab little place as it's on an old building, but don't be fooled.  The food is always good. The staff are nice and they try to get you in and out quickly. They deal with mostly breakfast and lunch crowds. They also throw in daily specials to keep it fresh.

result.formatted_address: 301 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA

result.reviews.text: Service horrible. Food horrible. Don't recommend this place at all. The waiters don't care about the customers at all since the gratitude is already included.  Overall horrible experience. Never going again.
I really like this restaurant for the ambience and great people watching. Ate here after a Puccini opera by the San Francisco Opera Company. I would highly recommend for any evening.

result.formatted_address: 536 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA

result.reviews.text: #Hot #Rare Indian food in a comfortable nitelyfe setting. It's good stuff... the curries are rich, sizzlin' with spice and the tandoori is crispy and smoky. Take a seat on the second floor for the real experience. Ride this horse.
Party of 3 on a wed evening. We had very good and fairly attentive service. Food was tasty and facilities clean. Prices reasonable.

Oh my god! Best halal food in San Francisco, no wait, one of the best in the nation! My friends and I absolutely loved every dish we ordered and licked our fingers clean! You must eat here if you're in the Bay Area. From salads to naans, you will not disappoint. The servers are very knowledgeable and the vibe is authentic Indian. Even loved the textured plates which we ate on! I will always return here as long as they remain this freaking good!

Had an opportunity to have dinner in this restaurant as part of our group of tourists of Make My Trip USA Summer Trip of 2016  on 30 May 2016. Very bad experience of their indifferent attitude and poor customer service. We were forced to have buffet dinner in the Stainless steel partitioned Thalis  which had residual marks  due to prolonged  use and  were unhygenic and on being pointed out,  the owner refused to accept the same and was arguing that these  were machine cleaned  and perfectly alright.  The  owner refused to provide normal regular dinner plates  though the Ala carte customers were being served in the normal  dinner plates ,  Is this attitude is because  we were tourists and had no  other option and the dinner was organised through the tour operator ? The owner did not have the  courtesy of  providing the regular dinner plate to the complained customer atleast  and  this behavior  is nothing but poor customer service  and high headedness.  Over all a bad experience on the last day of the tour  while we had dined  in 10 different Indian restaurants during the tour of USA and had a wonderful hospitality in  remaining other restuarents. I DO NOT recommend the place due to poor customer service.
Panneer tikka masala was excellent..Naan wasn't as soft as I had hoped..overall descent place

Service was very friendly, but very very slow.

The food is excellent and the service superb. The owner let us come in 10 mins before closing if we agreed to order quickly so that the kitchen could close but when we got our food, he said we could take as long as we wanted. Totally awesome guy.
Felt a bit rushed in a half empty restaurant. The server asked for the beverage menu back when i was very clearly still looking at it. The olives on the Caesar salad were extremely strong.

This is a must try if you've never been and always a go to place for great, fresh "non-canned" food.  Leave your diet foods at the door and endulge in a wonderful atmosphere of fun, delious food but be sure to leave a little room for the desserts, their chocolate macaroons are out of this world, great for sharing with a friend😘😀

result.formatted_address: 300 Grove St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Jardinière

result.reviews.text: I am a wedding coordinator who had a wedding here. All of our guests had a wonderful experience here. With the amazing food, romantic ambiance as well as the excellent services and french style design, our couple had such a memorable biggest day here. Highly recommend!!!

There are no longer tasting menus, nor an extensive menu provided.; though new menu items appear every couple of weeks The restaurant now appears to cater primarily to the pre-theater crowd, to which we belong. We find the food  and wine to be excellent, and the service generally very good. If reservations are not available, one can dine in the bar area. I do wish Jardiniere would bring back its tasting menus and more extensive menu.

I felt that I should have liked this place a bit more than I did. I couldn't quite put my finger on why that was until I saw the old photos of the interior, which show it with an earlier bright and light colour scheme. That seems to fit the delicate and delicious food served here much better than the current dark décor. Anyway, the staff were very polite and helpful. Great spot for a pre- or post-show meal.

Came to try the Impossible Burger. They said they start serving it at 7:30 in the bar and lounge. Arrived at 7:45 and they said it was sold out. $20 valet said they couldn't refund us even though the car was still outside. 

No thanks.
We got quail and short rib with four gras terrine and fried squash and all were very good esp the short ribs.  The panna cotta was very good.  The staff was very friendly as well.

result.adr_address: 200 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.formatted_address: 200 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Cafe Asia

result.reviews.text:
For museum food, it's more than acceptable! Sure, I'd rather eat in one of the cheaper restaurants outside, but sometimes I'm just one big ball of lazy. If I'm already in the museum, I won't venture out. Lunchtime seems to be the peak when all the tables inside appear full, and the line is long and bustling. Surprisingly, by the time you get through the line, there are tables ready. On a sunny day, there's outdoor seating that one should also take advantage of. 

The food can be a little on the luke warm side because everything is prepared already. They just throw it together when you place the order. It saves them time, and you don't have to wait too long for your food. Everything is served in the most adorable dishes. Condiments available include Thai chili sauce and Sriracha! YUM!

Surprisingly good food and value for a museum cafe.  Dim sum basket was 8 pieces for 8.5$.  Lentil soup was great comfort food.  Thai iced tea and blackberry lemonade completed the meal.  Veg noodles and pork dishes available.
Nice cafe in the museum
very good clam chowder.
oh, l miss this place

result.reviews.text:
I've had good experiences here and bad experiences. Generally the service can be pretty slow or inattentive.

On the bright side, the food can be pretty good. It's one of my favorite burgers in the city. I like the saigon hot wings, too.

Only three beers on tap.

Huge crowd of law students and city/state workers since it's right next to UC Hastings law school, city hall, four courthouses, the federal building, and a bunch of other civic buildings.
Tasty cocktails,  good food (some dishes were great,  others were just ok), walking distance to the theater, friendly wait staff.

The salade nicoise they served me yesterday for lunch was disappointing. I felt like the old "where's the beef?" lady, except in this case it was "where's the fish?" There could not have been more than 1.5 oz of tuna in there. It was high quality tuna, but still. The other ingredients included one egg, four olives (no more, no fewer), probably around 15 green beans, and 7 cups of lettuce. 

I was so hungry when I got back to work that I went to Starbucks and ate a turkey bacon muffin to supplement the meal.
Excellent selection of beers on tap and bourbon. Great food. Always a few vegetarian items on menu. Only a few blocks from civic center muni and bart.
Food was decent but not great.

result.formatted_address: 333 Fulton St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Pläj Restaurant

result.reviews.text: The only Scandinavian restaurant in San Francisco. Beautiful and delicious small shared and larger plates. I was expecting to be overwhelmed with flavor but they do a great job of keeping the dishes very well balanced. The dishes change seasonally but I had amazing oysters and foie gras on my last visit.
Amazing food just everything was great! A little hoity toity for me but I mostly kept it classy lol

This place will almost certainly be a positive and interesting experience for non-Scandinavians.

As a Scandinavian I was not impressed. For instance, the Danish open faced sandwiches were served on a sweet Swedish style bread very different from what you get with traditional Danish open faced sandwiches. If you are from one of the Nordic countries and you want to treat a friend or colleague to your local cuisine you are much better off cooking at home (particularly given the prices of this place). 

Also, I woke up the next morning with food poisoning.
Great, interesting food.  The space has a bar and a nice fireplace.  It is a windowless space but it is also quieter than most places in SF.  Nice wine list, too.
Astounding Swedish Cuisine! Special in every imaginable way. The Herring Platter is out of this world. You will walk away wanting to become Swedish!

result.adr_address: 390 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102-3609, USA
result.formatted_address: 390 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Gateway Croissant

result.reviews.text: We had our order delivered (Eat24).A very decent place to order breakfast or lunch.  We ordered croissant egg/ham/cheese sandwiches (croissants were large and super flaky), ordered an egg salad sandwich (good, good portion),  the apple fritter was excellent, and the smoothies are definitely worth a shot for a quick snack.  Will definitely order from here again.

I just happened to be in the area making some time for an appointment, and dropped by to have a little something. I had a ham and cheese croissant that was substantial and delicious. The service is good and corteous, and the place is kept very clean. The clientele can be very ecclectic, but that's San Francisco for you!

Gateway Croissant is a great place to grab a snack, cup of coffee or sandwich. It is open 24 hours &  they keep the store very clean. Here they serve 5 types of coffee and you can purchase a large coffee for less than half the price of a cup of Philz coffee across the street. The employees are attentive & friendly. My friends & I nicknamed one longtime employee the "Oh, hi!" guy after the way he greets customers.

I love making a pit stop at Gateway late at night or when I'm up early in the morning... They're always fresh and delicious. Several types of coffee, drinks, chocolate milk... And best of all are the neon signs that flicker and cast a soothing glow.

The donuts were excellent, and friendly service. The guy who works at the counter knows me since I was 3. I recommend this place as a excellent donut and coffee shop with friendly people, and a fair amount of seating.

result.adr_address: 395 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.formatted_address: 395 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Golden Era

result.reviews.text:
Vegan Restaurant. 
I am not vegan but that was really delicious at reasonable prices and good service.

My wife and I visited San Francisco recently and found this wonderful place.  The food is excellent, the service is quite good and the place is clean, spacious and modern.  We tried the bird's nest (noodles), the chef's treats and the rice, can't remember the name, all delicious.  The only complain I have are the surrounding streets.  We stayed near Union Square and the first walk to the restaurant was not nice at all, quite dangerous actually.  We found alternative routes that were better the following visits to the rest.  But nothing that could be considered as a negative review for the restaurant itself.  Well deserved 5 stars.

The tamarind appetizer was straightforward--a big pile of mock meat in sauce. Some parts of the pile were hot, while others were not. Perhaps it was heated in a microwave and then stirred? 

I liked my spicy Vietnamese soup better. While the broth was milder than the name implied, the flavor was more savory and rich than in a typical vegetarian broth. I enjoyed the many types. of protein in the soup. 

For dessert I had mango with sticky rice. A nice sized pool of rich coconut cream made this better than what most restaurants serve, but not much better.

Pleasant if sterile interior--sort of like the cafeteria at a not-too-fancy tech company. 

Staff seemed nice, but language barriers made it hard to communicate.

Horrible experience,  terrible hospitality and we all got deathly ill. I used to feel better about Golden Era, but after my last experience not so much. We show up and they said there were no tables, we sat for 45 minutes with multiple tables available and a couple of ladies walk in and get seated immediately. Not until I mentioned something did they finally give us a table. I had a horrible case of the runs and vomiting all night almost went to ER.
Your usual asian food , but with lot's of plant protein. Good confort food

result.adr_address: 380 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.formatted_address: 380 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Elephant Sushi

result.reviews.text: Elephant Sushi looked like an interesting place so I decided to try it. I am very familiar with this type of food, therefore I could tell that it was going to be good. This time I had the Spicy Trio Sashimi, which was perfectly coked & seasoned. This place is not cheap so if you  are looking for a cheap place you should head somewhere else, but definitely worth it.

Um...a guest from the mid-west wanted sushi in the area after a case and this place came up...reasonably priced and there were a fair amount of folks inside and it was ok.  umm...personally don't know what it might be like at night...but um..lunch was fine during a week day.

It's nice to see that Elephant Sushi at Golden Gate has existed longer than its predecessors.  It's in a little crevice in the Tenderloin, so it's easy to pass by.  But you'd be missing out on some seriously fresh fish.

I ordered a build-your-own sashimi bowl with salmon, tempura shrimp, tofu inari, and seaweed salad.  It was $14, and it increases if you want to add more toppings.  I also opted for the free garlic soy sauce.

I enjoyed my bowl and it was really filling.  The rice was cooked and seasoned well, and the salmon was fresh.  The tofu inari was just the skin, and the seaweed salad added a textural balance.  The tempura shrimp is smaller than what you get at other places, but it was fine for me.

I ordered it to go, but if you eat inside, be prepared to be in tight quarters.  It's very small with one large table and a few smaller tables.  There is outside seating, but the smell of the Tenderloin won't do you any good.

If you really want to stretch your dollar with the sashimi bowls, order it with all fish.  I had about 4 pieces of salmon in mine.

My only 2 issues were that the portions were a little low for the price and the area it was in. I know there is hard to find real estate around SF, but it was pretty tight with less than 15 people seating inside.

Overall, sushi is pretty good, but the need to expand the menu a bit to make the price worth it.

Has 4 different kinds of sashimi bowls. All priced at $12. You are able to customize your own sashimi bowl as well. There is a different price for your own bowl. The current 2 most popular sashimi bowls are number 1 (salmon, snow crab, avocado, "walu butter fish") and the spicy trio (spicy tuna, spicy scallop, spicy salmon & avocado). 

The wait time for my order was 10 minutes during lunch hour rush. Pretty reasonable time especially for this area when all the city workers swarm out for lunch. The lady who was ringing up my order was friendly, conversational and provided great customer service. She offered me a seat while I waited for my order. 

The sashimi bowl was beautifully put together and fresh seafood. No imitation whatsoever. For the portion size, it is decently priced for the fresh fish.The free miso soup for checking which normally costs $3 was not from a box, but actually cooked. There were huge slices of soft mushrooms and the broth was not salty.

Quick service, great customer service and an awesome new addition to this neighborhood. I'll be back to try the other sashimi bowls as well the other items the restaurant serves. This is my new lunch spot!

Good sweets and coffee - great alternative to Starbucks with better baked goods.

result.reviews.text:
Well...this is a good, fast and close Chinese place for when fussing children want Chinese FAST!!!! or let's 
Think...little disposable income after paying $4,000 to get the German vehicle fixed and still have to pay mortgage, hoa, auto home insurance...I am broke and I handed to much
Good food, good value, good selection and convenient location.

If you're on a budget, but want a meal that will get you full, the two-plate combo here is the way to go.  It's typical take-out Chinese food: chow mien, fried rice, general tso chicken, etc.  They also have chow fun, about one to two veggie dishes, and some dim sum options.  A two-plate combo is around $6, while a three-plate is $8.

There are a few places to sit, but the restaurant is across from the 19 bus stop, which brings in some characters.. best to take it to go if you can.

They also have a "happy hour" where the three-plate combos are sold for the price of two.  "Happy hour is from 3pm to 5pm.
Great tasting food, and heaps of it, for really good prices. The service is friendly, this place is so good I travel all the way there just for some General Tso's Chicken. It also serves dim sum.
Love it, go already 3x a week.

result.adr_address: 299 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 299 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Azúcar Lounge

result.reviews.text:
I love this space. I think it's close to perfect for a bar lounge. However, on almost every occasion, the service and/or the food, has been lacking. :-( Great place to hang though!

Try at your own risk.

My buddy Bob-o and I spent all day researching the best Mexican place in CA. We walked a very long while and arrived at Azúcar Lounge exactly at 5:30. We were the first ones there and by 6PM the place was packed. I ordered the lobster tacos special, which turned out to be intended for two people. It was one of the best meals I've had in my brief time on this Earth. Bob-o enjoyed his meal too.

The wait to get a table here was rather long, and there is not a large bar at which to wait. Once we were in and seated, the food, service, and drinks were great. The carnitas were a little watery, but the quesadillas more than made up for it.
We came to visit from Washington DC and Orange County, Jason welcome us and made our experience a great one for sure. Azucar has great food great service. I certainly recommend it!

Taco Tuesday is all you need to know. Bottomless tacos, and relatively cheap pitchers of margaritas. Other days...the prices are a bit steep, but Tuesday makes everything okay. Be warned, it can be busy, so if you have more than a couple people, you might want to make a reservation.

result.adr_address: 294 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 294 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Kama Sushi SOMA

result.reviews.text: First time eating here. Was early, so there was happy hour prices for some appetizers, which was pretty good. Restaurant was reasonably quiet when I arrived, and service was fast. Had some fried appetizers and a tekka roll. Roll was average. Fried things are better here. Service got slower as more people come, which I expects. All in all I would say 3.5 stars but have rounded up to 4.

Had a great meal with friends here for an early Sunday dinner. We were in the area and looking for something casual and fun to eat at. We arrived for happy hour here and got a great deal (for San Francisco pricing) on a lot of small plates and drinks. We eventually transitioned into their main dinner menu and shared a few rolls and rice plates. The service was really awesome: attentive, polite, and friendly! It came out to be around $40 a person and we left happy and full.

Come for their happy hour hot sake, butabara skewers and tuna tataki!
Great place to call your regular sushi spot. Good sushi, good Ramen, good undon and good prices. Very cosy and clean.

Pretty good food, pretty horrible service.

Came in around lunch time on a Wednesday with a friend. We were seated immediately and given menus, then promptly ignored for quite some time. We finally flagged someone over so we could order. I asked if it was possible to get the chirashi over mixed greens instead of rice, and I was told no, but no other suggestions were made. It wasn't until I asked to see the menu again (another 10 minute request) that they suggested the seafood salad for me... essentially, chirashi on greens. Oy.

On the bright side, the food was great. I appreciated the free edamame to start the meal and the fish was incredibly fresh. A healthy amount of fish with delicious dressing over fresh greens.

It took another 20 minutes to get the bill and pay, and the servers weren't particularly friendly. I'll likely come back since the food was good, but only when I know I have awhile to spend there.

I had a relatively bad experience here server-wise. I came with 4 people and our food orders all came out at drastically different times. Then, the final order, which was about 20 minutes after teh rest of us, wasn't right! We ended up staying well over an hour for our lunch break just to make sure everyone had gotten food and had time to eat it.

result.name: Bar Agricole

result.reviews.text: This restaurant is tremendously fun, always a great experience. The place is super vibrant and has a variety of nice spaces - outdoors, bar and indoor tables. The drinks menu is extensive, with great options in every category. The food is really nice. And the service stands out as exceptional and personal - the staff seem to quickly remember you and go out of their way to make you feel welcome.

Lamp chops were perfect. The quality of the lamb meat was high. Very tender. The carrots and small potatoes pulled the whole dish together. Also had the rani broccoli. Liked the spice added to the dish.

I did not understand that this was a "no tipping" restaurant so I was reallly upset about the prices at first. However, once I understood that tips were included in all prices it seemed much more reasonable. I enjoyed the food and the wine here. It's definitely not a casual place by any means but the decor is beautiful and there are some truly delicious dishes. I loved the brussel sprouts, mmmmmm...
Bad service ok food overpriced

Bar Agricole's menu is always fresh, because they base each day on what's available at the local market. The ambiance, the service, the architecture, the music, the drinks, the patio, and of course the food, make this a true San Francisco gem. Recommended for date night, dinner with colleagues, or a the private room downstairs for larger dinner events. Their tea is made from fresh herbs in their on site garden. And for drinks, the Planters Punch never lets down.

result.reviews.text: Very reasonable prices especially for the city. The BLT was outstanding with nice thick bacon. Service was quick and staff was very nice. Would definitely come back
The lady here was very nice, the sandwitch was delicious and a good price. Definitley a classic sandwich sub shop with chips and soda and also popular with folks in the neighborhood.
Love this place! This is my go-to place for a decent sandwich. They have several options and mostly all of them that I've tried are delicious.
Support local small business, Chris & his crew make great food served in generous portions.  Quick & efficient.
Good burgers. Arrive early usually a long wait because so many people come here. If you can phone in your order. The staff is super friendly.

result.adr_address: 1309 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 1309 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Chantal Guillon Patisserie

result.reviews.text: One of the better gelatos I've had in bay area. Tried a medium gelato with two flavors, orange blossom and passion fruit. The quantity was enormous for the price ($4.50) and the service was top notch. Place looked hip and modern. Overall a good spot for casual dates.
Sweet Lord how I wish this place was open even till just 1pm on Sundays lol incredible food and I'm disappointed every Sunday lol I bet they would absolutely SLAY brunch.

Uhhhh so apparently I have lived next to a really good macaroon shop and pastry shop for the last year. During the last year, I have learned how to bake all sorts of French pastries because my husband loves them and we couldn't find any good pastry shops. 

...
Sigh.
Facepalm.

So we finally made the trek out (by trek I mean a 5 minute walk) and ended up here. Holy smokes it makes an impression when you enter. It feels like you walked out of the ghetto into some upscale European museum designed by Apple (pure white everywhere).

There are beautiful, large croissants and giant quiches filled with different flavors, in addition to substantial salad options and decadent-looking sandwiches. And then there are beautiful rows and columns of macaroons in pastel colors. 

We got a fig and blue cheese quiche (these aren't dainty nor small - they are pretty massive as quiches go) and a chocolate croissant, in addition to two coffees (come with free ice cream bites that are covered in a chocolate hard shell - like a very fancy 1000X better klondike bite), and two macarons (almond amaretto and rose lychee).

Quiche had a buttery crust and was extremely filling. The croissant was buttery, flakey and perfect - chocolate inside was definitely a dark chocolate. The choco-marshmallow ice cream bite was uh-mazing (much better than the italian pistachio but I think that's a matter of taste), and the macarons were chewy and light (but I fell in love with macarons at Pierre Herme in Paris and I still prefer those). I liked the almond one better and my husband liked the rose one better. Go figure.

Will definitely be back.
Such a beautiful shop! The food is really good. I had the pate dish and it was fantastic.
I love this place!! Not only are the macaroons amazing (they have seasonal flavors so there is always a new one to try!) but their lunch is great too. They also serve afternoon tea.

result.reviews.text: We went for the show, but left pleasantly surprised about the food. The food was actually really good, and the family-style course serving meant there was always food on the table, but not a bunch of dishes. The cocktails were also pretty good, if maybe a bit too sweet. The show was great, too!

The food was very good. But people mainly come here for the show. Its a burlesque type show where the transgender servers will get up on the bar to dance in between courses. Unfortunately this makes it hard to get drinks while they're putting on their show - which would have probably made the show a bit more fun. I suggest ordering a lot of booze up front so you can enjoy the show with a drink in hand.
Most gorgeous girls in the world. Super fast service, totally delicious food. We had 14 course meal. Dancing afterwards. Would give it 10 stars if I could!
This place is amazing !! The shows are great, but the food is even better. 100% recommended
great food, so much fun,  BEAUTIFUL trans women!

result.adr_address: 1192 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 1192 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: F8 Nightclub & Bar

result.reviews.text: Expensive but cool crowd, loud music
Damn boring. Took the cover charges which when we asked before paying was told that it can be used for drinks but later they denied. Horribly boring at least today on a Saturday night !
I love the smaller DJs that play here, but it can sometimes get too packed. The security is usually very respectful and the staff accommodating.
Nice workers for a bar of this type. Strong drinks. Good sound system at least when I was there.

Wasn't sure what to expect at first. A decent entree fee of $30, two rooms to choose from, fascinating models and great djs...had an inspiring and psychedelic experience. Can't wait to come again. Went on Halloween and it wasn't too crowded and you could really let loose and be yourself.

result.adr_address: 1489 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 1489 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Basil Canteen

result.reviews.text:
What We Ordered
- Dtum Yum Goong
- Gai Gra Prao
- Pad Se Ew

Really overpriced Thai cuisine...not sure how authentic it is either but, it was really good! The Dtum Yum Goong had good flavor but, no that many shrimps.. tons of mushrooms. The Gai Gra Prao was my favorite! It was wok-fried minced chicken with green beans, chili, & fresh basil. Perfect with rice and probably better as a  lettuce wrap. The pad se ew was good but, you need to be really bad to mess that up haha. I don't think I would be back but, I learned something new that night. Need to find more places with Gai Gra Prao. :)

I've ordered delivery from here most of the time, but recently dropped into their actual location. They have great food, and a nice open ambience in the restaurant with a bar in the corner. Large tables should accommodate a group pretty well. They also have a solid happy hour with drinks and small bites, which I thinkkkk runs from 5 to 7, but check the facts on that one first.

We had a bachelor party of 14 guys here, they offer a great prefix menu with affordable price. The food was great and everybody left with their bellies full. The atmosphere and decor is very casual, cool and trendy, I would highly recommend this place. Good cocktails too! 🍹🍺🍸🍷
The BBQ ribs are amazing. A little bit of spice, sweet, and crisp texture make these ribs stand out. The small plates are priced lower during happy hour too.
Good Thai food at reasonable prices. Place is nice and clean. Friendly staff.

result.adr_address: 375 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 375 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: DNA Lounge

result.reviews.text:
Its a really odd nightclub but that being said it is a lot of fun. Expect to pay a cover and once inside pay for really crappy overpriced drinks. Watch your phones as there have been a lot of thefts here lately (most SF bars fall into this category). Also watch your drinks, drinks here are so expensive that seasoned patrons will snatch drinks when you arent looking. 
Great part about this place are all the different venues within the club. No matter what music you like to party to they will have something that you'll like.

Fun place. I've only been on Saturdays for Bootie mashups and they usually have several different rooms with different types of music to cater to most tastes (main stage for the mashups, a trap room, dubstep, EDM, and maybe others). There's a pizza place right next door attached to the venue for late night bites. Can get crowded depending on the mashup.

Not a bad venue, just not very memorable. Think "House of Blues" without the slip shod favela chic that gets Dan Aykroyd all a flutter. Sound quality is on point. Seriously, their engineer must be grizzled and blind Jedi master to get those levels into the sweet spot. Staff was largely indifferent.

I had a good time but I find the crowd of Polk street bars and clubs to be a little better. I was paranoid the whole time about my phone getting stolen as I had read multiple reviews on Yelp warning about cell phone theft there. There are signs posted all over inside and outside about not flashing your phone if you can avoid it because it makes you a target.  It is a bit dinghy.

Enough of the bad. The dj was fun and played hopping mash ups. My feet never stopped moving. There is a photo booth upstairs to have fun in. There is also an adjoined food joint next door serving pizza, sandwiches, coffee and more.
This is a great venue. It's close to food trucks, has its own pizza place, and serves drinks. What more could you want?

result.adr_address: 371 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-4313, USA
result.formatted_address: 371 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: DNA Pizza

result.reviews.text: Great coffee! I was surprised too, but worth a visit. Didn't try their pizza, but I did notice they have gluten free and vegan options!

Only giving 4 out of 5 based on the choice of toppings. Although the ones they have are great, there is only one meat option, pepperoni. Other than that, its BYOB, our server was amazing, she actually took our beers and put it in a fridge for us and when we ran low, grabbed them and filled our glasses. How great is that! The sauce is outstanding, the crust thin a crisp with a nice char taste. Cal zone was also pretty legit.All in all now in my top 5 with L & B's, Luzon, Di Fara's. Up next Roberta's & Paulie Gees!

If you are seeing or playing a show at DNA Lounge, it is very convenient to go here. But it is pretty pricy for just decent pizza. They do serve Speakeasy beers, though, whereas the inside venue doesn't - and you can bring the beers into the venue so that's a plus.
Way over priced and horrible service
Who doesn't love pizza at 2 am. Sure it's a little pricey but it is great. The music played in the dining area is fun and again, pizza at any time of day. Drunk food win!!!

result.adr_address: 498 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 498 9th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: L'acajou Bakery and Cafe

result.reviews.text:
Just came in a few minutes ago. One employee working who kept looking at me but no greeting or service brought to the counter. About five mins in as a line was growing a man came to take my order. The coffee requested was tepid, watered down, and disappointing. 

The storefront was dirty ( tables with food empty drinks  trash etc littering them and the floor) and needed stocking. 

I give it two stars for the decor, though not clean it was pretty.

Best baked goods since Tartine!

Now, don't get me wrong. There are a few places in town that are sharing that second place spot (No one beats Tartine), such as Hey, Cookie and Pinkies on Folsom. However, I've been to L'acajou Bakery twice now and both times I've been more than pleased. Morning buns, cookies, muffins...all AMAZING. From a muffin with espresso baked in, to a chocolate chip cookie with crystalline ginger sprinkled in. Wow. Good stuff. Complimented by the most reasonably priced cup of Ritual Coffee ($2) you'll ever find. Which was equally amazing by the way. 

Holy Crap! Did I mention the hot food? I had a Moroccan Lamb sandwich that knocked my socks off. DAMN. Good brunch menu too!

I took off a star because the owner is ALWAYS there and he looks/acts like he hates everyone and everything. Kinda puts a damper on it.
I have a biweekly lunch with my friend here and quite enjoy it. Occasionally they seem a little understaffed and the food can take some time as a result, but it's not too long a wait.
Lamb sandwich.   Nuff said

love love love the pear scone!  im not a scone aficionado (id rather have bacon) but twas definitely not the typical scone that you need to dip in coffee for an hour to chew.  

got the breakfast sandwich w/ the recommended spicy slaw (reminiscent of bakesale bettys slaw) ~ and since its laced w/ dijon, i must return to see what other plates are adorned w/ my fave condiment.

liking the look of the salads, im hoping to have the opportunity to get a lacajou vegan, people watch while using their free wi-fi.

result.reviews.text: I really like the pho here. Unfortunately the space is less than ideal. It's always super cold. Also they have a really old fashioned credit card machine that takes forever. There is often a realllly long line that takes a while to get through. That being said, it's a solid choice for a good lunch if you manage to avoid the line.

A great no-frill Vietnamese shop in SoMa. The Bun Bo Hue can be a little oily, but has a clear, clean flavor. The brisket is soft and delicious. Fast service makes up for total lack of decor - a totally respectable lunch spot!

Sunrise Cafe doesn't look like much on the outside or even after stepping in, but you're in for a treat if you love Vietnamese food.  Their meats are grilled to perfection and seasoned just right.  It's been too warm outside for me to try the Pho, but the Bun, Banh-mi and Cha Gio are delicious.  If you have time to spare, grab a Vietnamese iced coffee.  I'm really impressed by the service as well. If only they stayed open later for dinner... :)
The place to get a banh mi Vietnamese sandwich in SOMA. The grilled pork one had really delicious meat and I eat a lot of pork banh mi sandwiches...
Favorite lunch and pho spot. The spicy pho tai sate can't be beat

result.adr_address: 320 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-4314, USA
result.formatted_address: 320 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA

result.reviews.text: Absolutely amazing... This place is a hidden gem.  The inside is not at all pretty but omg the tacos were so good! The manager or owner happed to be there and explained that the tortillas were non GMO the fish was wildcaught and the beef was grass fed.. besides those facts it tasted amazing and the portions were generous! Will definitely be coming back.
AMAZING tacos for only $3.50! They give you generous portions of high quality meat and toppings. I highly recommend the fish tacos!
They burritos are amazing believe me im from Mexico
Good fast food, I like there burrito, and the sauerkraut sausage
abfab

result.name: Bergerac

result.reviews.text: My drink here was surprisingly tasty! The atmosphere was a bit strange on a mid week night. Rap and hip hop blasted on the speakers of this interesting looking bar. The only other patrons of the bar seemed to be a group of the bartenders friends. The TV seemed tuned to some sort of very softcore porn. Not my scene but certainly someone else's.

Great music. The guy who greeted us on the door was the best part of the evening, really polite and helpful! The waitress was inexperienced and got our drinks order wrong and pretty much walked away when we tried to explain the situation.

Cute little cocktail bar. Friendly bartenders, yummy bites (oysters, deviled eggs, fries, chicken tenders...), casual but cozy ambiance.

Local tip: check out their two-fer Tuesdays for a BOGO deal.
This place is uber gudaitis. Great cocktails and dancing on the weekend.
Awesome place! Fun tunes and drinks on Friday! A little slow on Saturdays. The men can be oddly aggressive on Fridays..

result.adr_address: 350 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 350 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Crepes A Go Go

result.reviews.text:
Great late night spot! Delicioius crepes, with fresh flavors. I really enjoyed my veggie crepe. There was a bunch of hot sauces to the side and we taste tested all of them. I can't remember which one was the best... but don't go for the La Victoria... that one was weird.

Anyway, happy crepe-ing!
Awesome late night spot. Loved house special #2 with sautéed spinach, caramelized onions and feta cheese!
Yummy late night food joint! Love the egg spinach crepe
Alway a spot to go too when you are out late night in SF. The crape will never disappoint you.
Been going here since 2005 . Love this place king lias and house special are my favorites . Bring everyone here for there San   Fran visit.

result.adr_address: 1175 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103-3999, USA
result.formatted_address: 1175 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Basil Thai Restaurant & Bar

result.reviews.text: This is solid 4 star restaurant. If you are staying in the civic center area it is easy to get to. The location in and around the restaurant was clean considering other areas nearby was not. We skipped lunch so we decided to have an early dinner and arrived when they opened at 5:30. We were the first to arrive but shortly after the restaurant began to fill up. It’s a small restaurant with simple décor. The servers were very friendly. For drinks we tried the ginger drop which is great if you like very tart drinks. We also tried the mango cosmopolitan, which was sweet and fruity. It was also very good. The food was served hot and came in large portions. We shared an order of spring rolls and crab fried rice. They were both very good but the crab fried rice was better than any I have had before.

Best Thai food in SOMA. Plates are small to moderate size but the flavor is good.  They serve Thai ice tea with coconut milk and I highly recommend the pumpkin curry with brown rice.  Usually crowded so make reservations or come on a non standard dinner night.

Really nice place. Good atmosphere and vibe. 
Food is very good and comes in big portions. 
Service is fine.
Amazing food.  Got duck puff pastries and lamb curry.  Pastries were amazing.  Sweet crunchy outside, savory and tender duck stuffing.  Lamb Curry was so good.  Nice and tender lamb, curry spot on.

Vegan/vegetarians beware! They give every table puffed rice wafers that are actually shrimp chips; they didn't warn me and I had to ask what was in them (after eating 1 D: ).

That being said their vegetarian dishes are decently priced and very good. They have a few dishes that you can't really get at other Thai places that are delicious. But if you want Thai and don't want to worry about vegan/vegetarian I would go to Thai Idea (vegan thai)

result.reviews.text: The chorizo tacos are the best. They are a little spicy and have fried potatoes in them and simply the yummiest chorizo tacos around.

result.reviews.text:
great variety.
hot soup.
good service.
fantastic location.

My favorite is the veg smokey split pea.

If you're in the market for wholesome soup, then this is the place for you.  Staff is very knowledgeable about the menu and can advise you exactly what the soup is made of.  I tried the smoky pea soup and was not disappointed.  Walked away with a "happy belly" and a wallet which was not much lighter than when I entered.

Definitely try their mexican tortilla soup and the turkey chili. Skip the tomato, potato, and chicken noodle. I like that they always have signature soups but rotate a few different ones daily. You can go online to see what's being offered. This location is tiny with no seating so prepare to take it to go.
I found this soup place and it's amazing. Very fresh and good selection of organic soups! Try smokey split lentil soup! worth it
I love their Mexican Tortilla Soup.  I was amazed the first time I had it, and would recommend it to anyone.

result.formatted_address: 235 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Lee's Deli

result.reviews.text: Good for a quick lunch. Not for the health conscious. But great greasy, flavorful and warm Chinese food. A small bowl could easily cost 6$. Eatsa across the street offers healthy options for 7$
I eat here at least 2x per week since it's so close to my office. Fast service, decent food, wide selection, fair prices - what's not to love?

Lee's has several locations in the City, but this is my favorite. Every weekday the salad bar has a terrific selection of hot and cold foods, so one can have something different everyday. Food from the salad bar is weighed and one pays by the ounce. Very easy to manage portion sizes to match your appetite. They also make custom sandwiches to order and Asian dishes to order. It's in the wonderful Neogothic building on Montgomery and the dining room has many original features from the financial world of San Francisco's yesteryear.
The maple bacon cronots is worth the trip here alone. One of the first places to my knowledge to offer the fabled cronot is SF.

result.adr_address: 220 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 220 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Freshroll

result.reviews.text: Had a great thia style bowl. I asked for extra Sriracha on it and they did not dissapoint. Yum!

This is a great place for a quick and delicious bite to eat. I usually get the sandwich with pork but the 3 rolls are also really solid.  Everything is made in front of you and you can customize on the spot. Think of a Vietnamese version of Chipotle.

They sometimes have pho noodle soup, which is great on a cold SF day.
One of the few healthy yet cheap eat out options in the Financial District. However that also comes with the fact that the lines are often longer than other places.

This is a modern Vietnamese fast food, where they assembly your custom Vietnamese rice or Rice Vermicelli Bowl or Spring Rolls. The general concept is just like Chipotle but it is Vietnamese food. The lines moves slow and there are usually a lot of people during lunch time. I got the pork over brown rice with everything on it along with two sauces I picked. Overall, it is fresh, light and unique. They also have Vietnamese coffee so that is a bonus. Will be back for more when I don't feel like a greasy sandwich or light salad.

Pretty good rolls... Not quiet like a traditional Pho restaurant but good and fresh none the less (and very quick - if you get there at 11:35am!).  Similar to Chipotle concept.  I gave them 4 stars instead of 5 because the music was a bit too loud and the seating area was scarce.

result.adr_address: 348 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 348 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Diller's

result.reviews.text: Solid, established deli. Good sandwiches, great prices, decent coffee, fast service for your sandwich order, and the salad bar is very fresh - not huge, but a good selection of quality ingredients.
You gotta try the Turkey Salsa on Dutch Crunch with Pepperjack cheese...now that's a sandwich!  My mouth is still burning...but in a good way!  LOL
Hot as hell inside though...
El lugar tiene mucha historia.la arquitectura  es excelente

result.adr_address: 360 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 360 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Credo

result.reviews.text: The burrata here is the main attraction. So creamy and goes perfectly with the tomato and eggplant salad. The Garganelli is perfectly cooked and so creamy and nutty. A bit pricey.

Solid, consistent spot for business lunch downtown. Attentive and knowledgeable service makes for a welcoming experience. Credo offers a nice selection of contemporary Italian dishes in manageable portions. Great spot for something intimate/romantic after work as well.
Great ambiance and even better food. Many pasta options and a solid number of vegetarian options. Their cocktail menu is also pretty good. I was quite pleased with my experience here.
Nice little Italian restaurant in financial district. The food was excellent. Had some awesome chicken wrapped in prosciutto.

Great downtown lunch spot just a few blocks from the Montgomery station. Local and organic ingredients with plenty of options for vegetarians and omnivores alike. I highly recommend the seasonal butternut squash soup. The chop salad comes in two sizes and both are generously sized. Service is friendly and knowledgeable.

result.adr_address: 151 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104-4104, USA
result.formatted_address: 151 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA

result.adr_address: 101 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 101 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: La Fromagerie Cheese Shop

result.reviews.text: My favorite lunch spot in SF!! Their gourmet sandwiches are to die for- and I learned all products are from Europe or sourced locally! Today I took a duck salad, picture attached. The owners are from France so it adds to their wonderful charm, and their breakfast is super tasty as well. Pretty much the best place ever.

First visit. Had the La Toulouse sandwich and the salad for lunch just last week. Oh, so good. The bread, the cheese .... everything is just soooo good and works together. My daughter had the Californian. She really enjoyed her food, too. She at half the sandwich because she got too full. They have a  table inside by the window and a couple others outside for those looking to sit down to eat. Staff was super friendly and food prep was SUPER fast. 
Two sandwiches and two bottles of water ~$33.00 and worth it.

Beautiful presentation, excellent service, prompt delivery - and ohhhh the tapas plate was BEAUTIFUL and the cheeses so deliciously fresh with those fabulous Fig and Olive crackers....these  people are great!!!!  Give them lots of love so these stay in the hood!!
Great food. The italien sandwich is amazing and they're not picky on the quantity

Best cheese I've ever had.  The croissants here are freshly made and delicious.  The person behind the counter was very knowledgeable and super friendly.  I can't wait to go back and learn more about different cheeses.  They serve breakfast and lunch.

result.adr_address: 333 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 333 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Escape From New York Pizza

result.reviews.text: Great pizza and makes for a quick pickup during lunch hours.
Great at happy hour - I like to grab a beer (happy hour pricing!) and sit outside in the shade.

This place is alright - the location doesn't have much going for it, for eat-in; they have a small bar but you can't actually get service there, you have to get up and go around to the registers; the pizza is alright, best fresh when the crust is still soft, but can trend towards the thin-and-greasy end of the spectrum, and if you get an older slice the crust is hard and not good.
Great pizzas, would be great if they used different cutlery for Veg and non veg pizzas.
They have a lot of "odd" options, but their Hawaiian is pretty good. Large slices and decent crust.

result.adr_address: 8 Trinity Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 8 Trinity Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: the Golden West

result.reviews.text:
Tasty (pulled pork sandich)!!! I liked the fresh baked ban. 
Small choice of sandwiches. Little bit pricey  $$
Visiting from out of town. This place was packed. They were incredibly fast. Definitely planning to go back while it town. Next time gonna maul Matt cain.
I found this place by the smell! Delicious and friendly service
Small menu with amazing sandwiches, and very fast service.

The sandwiches are superb as everyone says (just like their sister restaurant, SENTINEL) but kinda small. It will leave a grown man still a bit hungry. My favorite part is the bread which is fluffy and baked in-house I think. GAHHH

result.adr_address: 116 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 116 Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Proper Food

result.reviews.text:
Want to pick up something quick and easy?

Proper Food is the way to go. They have pre-packaged meals for breakfast and lunch. A little pricy but the food is good. I personally love coming here for breakfast and picking up their SWEET POTATO NEST WITH BACON. It's $4 and it's delicious! 

The staff is friendly and they can heat up your food for you so it's nice and hot :)

result.adr_address: 300 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 300 Pine St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Señor Sisig

result.reviews.text: The "Señor" Sisig Burrito is heavenly.  I get it with pork.  The line is very long so my pro tip is to come on a windy/rainy day and have almost no wait. The dulche de leche cookie is worth trying at least once.

(I went here when it was in SOMA.) This is one of my favourite food trucks. Great place for some filipino fusion food. I like to get the senor sisig burrito with pork. It's a good portion of food for the price, and sometimes I find that I have to share it with someone just to finish it lol. The staff is friendly and can offer suggestions if you're unsure. If you want to try it and don't know where to find them, check their website for their scheduled truck locations :)
You guys should check out Beach Chalet at night! 300-400 people there playing Pokemon Go. Great business if ya ask me! Mass of people usually gets there 4pm - 3am

Food: 3
Decor: 2
Service: 4

Grabbed some food from here as soon as I saw the truck since I've been wanting to try it out for a while.

1. THE "SEÑOR" SISIG BURRITO with pork and fried egg
With Adobo garlic rice, pinto beans, lettuce, pico de gallo & our cilantro cream sauce
~Okay.

2. SISIG FRIES with chicken
Crispy shoestring French fries topped with nacho cheese, sour cream, guacamole, pico de gallo & picked jalepeños
~Pretty good. Tasted much better than it looked, although I felt rather guilty after eating more than half of it.

Service was friendly, and the food came out fast.

Senor Sisig, you're one of my favorite burritos 
Better than Taco Bell or el Torito
Your Cali burrito is oh so fine 
Your pork and fries are one of a kind 
If you want to go beast mode add an egg for one dollar
But watch out, ppl might start calling you a baller
It's ok because this burrito is pure bliss
Make sure you follow their location on Twitter or else you'll miss

Their pork and fries in their California burritos are pretty stellar. Still crispy even in that fat cylinder of goodness. Their nacho fries with their pork is also off the hook.  But one warning if you're on a diet or need to stay awake in the afternoon, don't get it.  Consider yourself warned.

result.adr_address: 120 Sansome St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.formatted_address: 120 Sansome St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Mixt

result.reviews.text:
Mixt Greens is one of healthiest and tastiest options for lunch in downtown SF. They are a regular rotation for catering options (at least 1/week), and remains a constant hit and fave of the office. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu. 

Props to the Sansome team for consistently providing great service both in-house and delivery. 

**Personal favorites: 
Salads: Maui (for variation: add soba), Cowboy, Madison, Bachelor, Dagwood
Sandwiches: Disco, Royale

**Make this mix: mixt greens, seared ahi tuna, pea shoots, fresh herbs, red pepper, cucumber, edamame, soba noodles, sesame soy dressing

I'm not much of a salad person. Or, rather, I'm not much of a "let me buy a salad for lunch" kind of person, so I've avoided places like Mixt Greens for, well, pretty much ever. Having binged a little too much on rich (literally and figuratively) food for too long though, I actually agreed to dropping by the last time my coworker suggested the place.

Working my way through the expected lunch crush, which wasn't so bad since the line moved quickly, I ended up ordering their Orchard salad, with dressing on the side. And, how was it? Enjoyable, for sure. Something I'd order again? Yeah, if I were in the mood. A place I'd frequent? Nah, definitely not. Something about paying ten bucks for a salad on the daily, when I could have a fully prepared hot meal instead just rubs me the wrong way.

***Accessibility Info***

Venue - Their main entrance has a couple steps, and is not at all accessible. However, there's an accessible entrance through the building to the right, which brings you in through their back entrance. During lunch hours, it can be pretty crowded, so you'll have to maneuver through the throng, to get to the end of the line (or, you know, be a jerk and cut).

Bathroom - Didn't try them.
Huge line, good quality but overpriced

Get here right when they open to avoid the long lines and design your own fabulous fresh salad from the millions of options.

If you can't get here early, they do have a cooler near the front door with some pre-made salads and then you can cut the "make salad" line and head straight to the register.  

Sometimes the salad makers don't seem to understand when I say "very light" dressing, but that's a minor quibble.

Solid make-your-own salad spot. Spending $12-16 on lunch is pretty much the norm in downtown SF nowadays, so not really sure why there are complaints about the price here. Long line, but it moved very quickly. Overall positive experience.

Convenient location, although they close at 3:30. For a late lunch just before closing tried the SF crepe and coffee, the cappuccino sure could have been better. 
Gonna come in for breakfast to try the cragel next time.

result.formatted_address: 22 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA

result.reviews.text: Groupon and this place have a great scheme going on. Groupon is for 49$ but you end up paying 25 more (in taxes + mandatory 18% gratuity -read fine print- plus some mandatory SF thingy). So, essentially this is not a deal at all coz final bill is anyways gonna be 76$. Very nasty move - Groupon+Cafe Bastille. NOTE: Free passive smoking services available. People smoke all the time within 5 feet of the place and by the end of the meal you have passively smoked cigarettes for an entire fortnight.
Found this place accidentally when walked in SF when it was raining. Food was good, service was OK. It is not very big inside and quite cozy.
Loved the food and atmosphere. Waiters and servers were super friendly and went the extra mile!! Would highly recommend it!
The service was good and efficient! Perfect for work day lunch with a big group. Food was good, portion was on the bigger side so sharing is recommended.

Good place to savor French cuisine. Not the real thing, but the closest one can come in the area, including the outside sitting. You can taste a fixed dinner sampler, or you can order whatever you like from the menu.  Free street parking after 6:00 can be found on side streets, while everyone else is trying to leave the city to go home.

result.adr_address: 40 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104-2802, USA
result.formatted_address: 40 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Plouf

result.reviews.text: Had the fish and chips, crab cake and garlic bread for take out. Liked the fish and chips, which had crisp batter and tasty fish meat. Thought the garlic bread and crab cakes were alright.

Only had one night in SF and I'm so glad we went here. Our hotel concierge recommend we speak to Franc who was wonderful. Food was outstanding an unbelievable fair. As someone who works in the industry you need to do yourself a favor and eat here!
I had the corn appetizer and the plouf mussels, and the were awesome. The staff was fantastic as well. I would highly recommend this place.

On a small street with a number of other restaurants. Place apparently specializes in seafood so it may be my fault that I ordered the lamb. In my defense, it is a small menu ( the wine list is much larger than the food menu) so I assumed that if on menu they would have gotten it right. Not so much. The lamb is more like a soup with a bone thrown in there. It was ugly looking and only slightly better tasting. Just a mess. Maybe fish better but I won't find out as I won't go back.
The mussels here are one of the best in the city. However other dishes on the menu aren't as impressive.

result.adr_address: 44 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104-2802, USA
result.formatted_address: 44 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: B44 Catalan Bistro

result.reviews.text: cute tapas place on very charming pedestrian hidden alley - felt like we were transported to a sidewalk bistro in europe, but food was just ok

Good tapas place. Strong bold flavors that leave you wanting more. Fortunately, there's good wine to wash it down with. Funky location in the Financial District that is quiet and out of the way in the evening.

I refuse to discuss value or specific dishes. No place has all perfect dishes and prices, ever. B44 has a great decor, unique setting, and serves very authentic food. It is a great place for a group of four or more to sample a wide variety of Catalan-derived food, without being rushed and while imbibing Spanish wines. Our party of four completely enjoyed our meal, and will return again for a solid Catalan experience
Great selection and tasty tapas.  Service was authentically a little relaxed and slow, but you probably aren't in a hurry if you're out for tapas anyhow.
I love their paella. It's a good place for a business lunch.

result.adr_address: 28 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104-2802, USA
result.formatted_address: 28 Belden Pl, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
result.name: Cafe Tiramisu

result.reviews.text:
I went here just because someone recommended the tiramisu, but the restaurant doesn't allow you order only desserts... So I tried out their zucchini fritters, I'm glad I did, I hadn't had zucchini fritters with some delicious italian sauce, it was real good. And the tiramisu that I went for, was pretty good - won't say the best tiramisu I've had but it sure was pretty good. I had another dessert, fried donuts with a chocolate dipping sauce - the choc sauce was delicious. 
They had some good wine selection, and a their service was real good.

Absolutely incredible. Can't believe this place doesn't have higher reviews. Superb house made pasta and you can tell the owner (Giuseppi) truly cares about his food. I come here everytime I'm in SF and it's always excellent.

Easily the best Italian food I've ever had in the states.  The homemade pasta is just perfect, with a subtle, yet slightly tangy tomato sauce.  It all melts in your mouth.  End with the panda cotta and all will be well.  The best part of this place is the venue.  You feel like you could be in Rome, Paris, Stockholm... use your imagination for any old European City.  The owner is proud of his restaurant and what he has done to grow in 25 years, and rightfully so!
Staff is amazing and I'm always surprised by all the unique selections. I've tried appetizers I never thought I would like and yet were delicious. Desserts are incredible.

Came here for a Sunday night dinner as we were in the area and decided to try a place on Belden Lane.

Started with the Bruschetta - this was okay - the tomatoes didn't have much flavor and it had some sort of white sauce on it that had a subtle taste of either aioli/mayonnaise or anchovy.  Didn't really stand out.

What did stand out was the Seafood Linguine, but unfortunately it stood out for less than positive reason: ie: where was all the linguine?!?.  It probably had about 2 oz of pasta mixed in with really tiny bits of seafood.  Italian restaurants should be generous on pasta, but in this case they weren't.  Also, they said they had handmade pasta, but it didn't seem to be any different than standard Barilla pasta (which isn't bad, but doesn't have the consistency of handmade, fresh).

Wife had the pappardelle pasta and said it was good.  She noticed how little my portion was and felt bad for me.

We ordered the tiramisu at the end - they make that there as well - it didn't stand out and, writing this a couple of days later, I can't really remember much about it.

Prices were high here, which wouldn't be bad if the food was worth it, but sadly it wasn't.

2 stars because I didn't like this place and I wouldn't come back.

result.reviews.text: Great little coffee shop with good specials every day of the week.
Place is crowded. They have good sandwich and soup options.

I considered 3 stars, but Prima delivers subpar sandwiches in an overly saturated sandwich district full of unique, fresh, high quality and sometimes high value options. While affordable, I had no desire to finish more than 1/2 a sandwich. The ingredients were decently fresh but the flavors were lacking. 

I might return for a smoothie (very popular item) or froyo but definitely not for sandwiches.

result.formatted_address: 215 Fremont St #2b, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA

result.reviews.text: Love this place for a variety of feel-like-home-made food. Their salad bar is really great. The sea bass is a must try. Also, I recently tried their chicken quesadila and it was to die for.
Great food, lunch buffet. Homestyle food from different cultures. Fair prices. Limited seating. I would highly recommend for lunch :)
Great variety of food, owner super nice.  Can't beat the quality or flavor here.

The food is great! Has a great mixture of mediterranean-inspired salad bar and sandwiches. I love how friendly the staff are. The only downfall is that they have a serious bottleneck when it comes to making their sandwiches. One sandwich will usually take a good 15 minutes.

I love this place, its my favorite spot for lunch in all of San Francisco.  They have a wide variety of food in their salad bar which is sure to please vegetarians and meat eaters.  The flavor will leave your taste buds very satisfied and the sandwiches are out of this world, packed with flavor and fresh ingredients.  They also serve warm wraps and have an entire Mexican food section that makes burritos and burritos bowls.  There is something for everyone here, do yourself a favor and try Fayala.

Taste food & good service.

result.reviews.text: They raised their prices by $1-$2 for each item, and lowered amount of food. Now it's not worth it to eat there anymore. The picture below shows food that cost OVER $20. The rolls are a bit smaller than they used to be which adds up. This meal used to cost around $15 and there was more food.
Why is their food always cold?!!  I have come here several times to spend down a gift certificate, but the food is always cold no matter what I get or what time I come.  Never coming back!

Avoid.

Ramen was MSG-ish and hard-cooked egg sulfurous. Oshinko in maki was not crunchy. Saba nigiri had bad texture. My friend couldn't eat his tonkatsu--he said it was unpalatably dry.

In some cities, this might have gotten two stars, but in SF there is no excuse.
Delicious bento box for a great value! I also love the sashimi samplers, the salmon here is the best. This is a perfect spot for lunch or for grabbing a quick bite and a beer after work.

Decent for the quality and price
Wish it was a dollar less for ramen, that'd be nice
But overall taste wasn't that bad
Looks pretty busy, so you know it ain't a fad

Ordered the spicy ramen pork noodles and it was decent, wasn't bad. Heard a lot of reviews dogging the food but it came out good, noodles were ok, good amount of meat and was great on a cold day.

result.reviews.text: The taste was bland...but liked only the boti chicken
Stale roti, mild food poisoning, flavor was good though
Never disappointed me. I don't like the nan, I don't eat it, but the rest is actually more than enough.

This is a great little place to grab lunch and then head to the Embarcadero to sit and enjoy the views.  They have the same 4-5 menu options to choose from daily, and most everyone gets it to go since they only have 1-2 tables.  Its about 2 blocks from great people watching on Embarcadero - fun to just relax in the sun and eat some yummy Indian food.

When lunch time beckons and you want the aroma of Pakistanian food envelopes you, check out Rotee Express. They make consistently good Masala and nice Rotees. While the serving size might be scaled back, the food is a must eat, must consume place if you seek Indian food during lunch around Financial District!

result.reviews.text: The specials are quite good however service isn't a strong point. I felt very rushed and pressured into a decision even though there was no one else in line. Charges extra for milk and beggars come in asking you for money. The food was at least tasty though.
Good breakfast at a reasonable price. The coffee was pretty good also.
Excellent food and service!! I enjoyed my meal here. Everything was fresh!!
Poor service, food isn't good enough to make up for it.

Sometimes they're really good, sometimes not so much.  Their pasta falls pretty flat, but the Steak Fajita Sandwich was great.  The servers have always been courteous and fast.  Yes they do concentrate on throughput, but so does every other restaurant of that type in the area at any food rush hour like breakfast or lunchtime.  

I very much like being able to order online.  No waiting.

result.reviews.text: Pretty great meal. The appetizers were great for sharing and the main I got was the pork loin. The portion was quite large and mighty tasty. Only gripe I had was the atmosphere. It was a little loud and a little packed. I understand that it's a popular place but they could remove a couple tables to make a bit more room to move around. Overall, a great place!
Love this place. Great food, great service, and awesome atmosphere. Usually come here at night and decided to give it a try for lunch. Had the North Carolina BBQ Sandwich. Awesome!
Liked the ambiance.  Food was decent.  Service was not great.

I visited Town Hall with my colleagues as a welcome lunch for new team members.

It's very nice inside, but the outside has a bit too much traffic/construction for my liking.

The food is great. I had a pulled pork sandwich that I will definitely get again soon.

Came here one day after work. It was very crowded, which to me is a very good sign. The bartenders knew many people by name and knew exactly what they wanted. The steak is awesome. Very upscale looking plating when it arrives. The tater tots were some of the most interesting tasting tots I've ever had. I'm not completely sure if I liked them or not but, they are definitely worth a try.

go for sub of the day...that's the best deal. if you want more cheap deals then subscribe for their coupons.

result.reviews.text: A great non-chain old fashioned cafe with great prices. Definitely my preferred spot to grab a quick coffee in the morning, and maybe a (turkey, egg, and cheddar bagel sandwich).
Their turkey sandwiches are delicious. Their turkey is shredded and moist, great sandwich in the financial district.

I got the tuna salad sandwich on Dutch crunch. Although, such a standard sandwich choice, I give  it 2/5 because I was deceived by their sandwich pricing: a sandwich costs $6.95 and $7.95 but with addition of cheese it's an extra $1. Not cool. Who asks for a sandwich with no cheese; does a burrito shop up-charge their customers a $1 for adding cheese. Cheese is a basic component of a sandwich as it is to a burrito.
These guys have the BEST roast turkey sandwich in the area.  They roast the turkey daily, then shred it for sandwiches.  Good sandwiches at a very reasonable price this close to downtown.
If you enjoy a packed sandwich then you will love their triple decker! I always get one of their hot sandwiches, it's good spot for lunch!

result.adr_address: 160 Spear St, San Francisco, CA 94105-1543, USA
result.formatted_address: 160 Spear St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.name: Tokyo Express

result.reviews.text:
This is a surprisingly large counter order Japanese restaurant. It is a good place to grab lunch during the work week. We arrived a little after 12 and there was a fairly long line although it moved very quickly.

I got the chicken katsu donburi. It was alright, but fairly bland.
Great if you are working in the area, but I would not make a trip across the city to go here.
The quality of food is mediocre, but you really can't beat the price in SF. Go if you want to fill up on cheap, affordable food.
Bearable Japanese food at relatively (financial district) cheap prices. Food to $ is definitely high, which is good for me! Food taste is average.
Favorite lunch spot in the city. Always keep me coming back for more.

result.formatted_address: 180 Spear St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA

result.reviews.text: The sandwich I had was hard. The bread was to staile the soup was plain. Not really your moneys worth.

Happened to stop by Heyday last week to pick up lunch. As a vegetarian, I was happy to see a good selection of healthy options. I chose s Moroccan chickpea salad and a lentil soup with red beans. Both of them were excellent for a reasonable price. The ambiance is sparse but nice.
Worth a visit if you are in the neighborhood.

One of my favorite financial district lunch spot! healthy and fast!
I love their smoked trout open face sandwich and their kale salad! It is on the pricier side a little for how much you get, then again it is quality food!

Sandwiches are small and not enough for a meal - tried the cauliflower sandwich - pretty lackluster - bread was hard, barely any seasoning in the sandwich! Also tried the Moroccan Chickpea salad - chickpeas were under-cooked and hard. This was my second time at Heyday. First time experience wasn't good either!
Great options, and everything is fresh and made daily. So there's always something to look forward to.

result.reviews.text: Decent selection of mediocre food. Salad bar has everything you need. Mediocre hot Chinese food. Decent in a pinch and not too overly expensive. Good for a quick bite.

Lee's deli, you're like the Swiss Army knife of Chinese food,
You got American, Chinese and even cronuts! Dude....
That's pretty stellar and I think you're a solid place
You price by weight so be careful how you stuff your face

This place has a LOT of different kinds of food. Got salad, Chinese food (you pick and pay for by weight) and sandwiches. They even were the first ones to serve cronuts in SF and I won't lie, they're pretty good. Good place to go!
Helloooooo food poisoning. Stay away if you value your stomach or general well being.

If you're in the area and craving Chinese food, you basically have to choose between here and Yank Sing. Lee's is, of course, the much cheaper option.

There's nothing extraordinary about this place, except for the endless stream of Celine Dion and Adele that they play for ambient music. Most of the food is served on hot trays (the salad area is cold, of course), and customers pay by the pound. Expect typical options that rarely change: rice, noodles, broccoli beef, egg rolls, orange chicken, etc. As for me, I usually go for the shrimp wonton noodle soup.
Good buffet lunch spread.

This place just opened and I live nearby. I thought I'd stop in after work and was told that there is no "Plain Brown" (or white) rice at this Chipotle. 

Not sure if the staff is just not properly trained (doesn't seem like it considering they knew it was because of cilantro) but it's incredibly disappointing and hopefully not something all new locations are doing.

result.reviews.text: Delicious food for a regular price in SF (but pricier than if in a different city). Nice atmosphere, easy ordering, but no seating in the restaurant.

This is my go-to spot when I need something quick, reliable, and good. It took me a few trips to get my order down, but I've decided on the Turkey Cranberry on Focaccia. I always think about changing up my order or tweaking the ingredients slightly, but I don't want to ruin a good thing. Quick, reliable, and good is all I'm looking for on some days.

No long and wordy review needed here. This place has some of the best cookies around. The flavors are pretty basic, chocolate chip, peanut butter, etc. That is fine though because they are consistently delicious.
Best sandwhich spot in SF in my opinion. Staff is amazing. And they take a personal interest in you. They learned my name quick. And I have an "older" name... so I was surprised.
Good lunch to go spot. The baked goods are amazing as well. They have online ordering which is super convenient.
