result.adr_address: 300 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 300 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Goat Hill Pizza

result.reviews.text: Delicious sourdough pizza! We've ordered takeout several times and it's always excellent. If you eat in on Monday's it's called community night which is like Brazilian Steakhouse style all you can eat. This format is nice because they cut the slices small so you can try all different types; I had eight or nine different slices! The staff was super friendly.

We were staying at a nearby vacation rental and had eaten at several establishments in the area. Gourmet style of pizza rather than your average chain pie and done very well. Sat by the window and looked out on 18th street. Busy energetic place but service was still very good.

Great servicr, great food. The curry mushroom soup was so good i couldn't stop. Bruschetta was very good.  Pizza was awesome crust just right not too think or thin, sauce not overpowering and toppings were fresh.
Very friendly staff. Excellent food. Great atmosphere. Would recommend.

Great family place!! I went here after a game on Sunday with my teen son.  2 slices of Pizza, meatballs and garlic bread plus a beer for me and soda for him and it was $18.  Attentive staff....great local place with great food!

result.adr_address: 317 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 317 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Papito

result.reviews.text: What a great spot for brunch/lunch.  Superb salsa.  Great tacos and the French toast is pretty good too. The sangria wasn't anything to write about.  Highly recommended overall.

The Papito special and the service were terrific. Their carne asada has flavor and the ingredients all seemed very fresh. I wish the special would have came with tortillas though. Make sure to ask for them if you like to roll your own little tacos.
Great fish tacos! The pork enchilada was really tasty too. Great little spot in Potrero hill!

Came here on a Tuesday evening with my aunt around 6:00pm. The place was empty and we were easily able to snag two seats at the bar.

The service was fantastic - we were greeted right away, and checked in on regularly, by the bartender/server. He made plenty of recommendations for us and let me try the sangria before ordering to be sure it wasn't too sweet (it wasn't). We ended up sharing a few dishes:

Ceviche: 5-stars. Super fresh with large, plump shrimp, onion, mango, cucumber, and avocado. Lots of citrus flavor and a really good kick to it. I couldn't taste any spice or pepper, so I don't know where the kick came from, but it left an awesome burn that didn't get in the way of the other flavors. Huge portion. This dish was the star of the night.

Mushroom quesadilla: 3-stars. Good but nothing adventurous or interesting. Cheesy, chunks of crunchy corn, darker, earthier flavors from the mushroom, but nothing really distinct. It was definitely a quesadilla with some mushroom and veggies, not a quesadilla that screamed mushroom or veggie first.

Hawaiano taco: 3-stars. The flavors ran together a bit, the tuna was bland and the textures made the whole taco mushy. Nothing remarkable.

Bajataco: 4-stars. The fish itself was really flavorful and well fried but not overly so. The onion on top provided a nice acidic cut to the taco but overall it could have used slightly more flavor, perhaps through chipotle aioli or something like that.

If I lived nearby, I'd stop in all the time purely for the ceviche. I'd probably come back to try other things, as I heard good things about the duck, but I wasn't blown away and I won't be going out of my way for this place.
Great neighborhood spot. Huge burritos, tacos, and fresh guacamole. Make sure you try the sangria and margaritas to accompany.

result.adr_address: 288 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 288 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA

result.reviews.text: seating was fast, its on 1st come 1st serve basis. Pho is called noodle soup but it tastes pretty good. I will definitely go back to try more things on menu.

As with most Vietnamese restaurants, I recommend a rice noodle dish, as it's what the culture's cuisine is known for. Here you can get most of the basic Vietnamese dishes. The seafood noodle soup hit the spot on a cool evening.
Very good Vietnamese food. Fresh tasting and creative. The place is small and there's often a wait.
Great lunch specials! The soup that comes with lunch is VERY sweet (lots of pineapple). I couldn't eat it. Everything else was really good.
Stopped in for a quick father/daughter lunch.  Great soups and vermicelli bowls, fast service.

result.formatted_address: 1469 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Mochica

result.reviews.text: Great Peruvian food. We had early reservation so it wasn't very crowded but by the time we left the place was packed. Great cocktails and delicious food. I wish I lived in the neighborhood. I would eat here all the time

Update: inconsistent service strikes again. Took the rating down from 4 to 3 stars.
After a very disappointing first experience a year ago (where our table didn't get any of the food we ordered, but others who sat down after us were), I decided to give Mochica another try.  This time we sat at the bar and I have to say the food was flavorful and delicious.  Hopefully, the second time is a more representative experience.

Stopped here with the hubs in search of a pisco sour. It's a must here. The food and service are great but the music changes from Spanish to remakes of US pop as the night goes on. Make sure to check out their new brunch menu on Sunday's.
Great Peruvian food with modern approach. A bit pricy but Worth it

I drove to San Francisco extatic, since I've never had the chance of visiting before. My first stop was good and it would determine the mood for the remainder of my day. First impression was awful was treated with such disrespect. Mind you I am traveling with my boyfriend who just happens to be Peruvian. Funny thing is they are so proud of serving Peruvian cuisine, but yet fail to treat ALL customers with some respect. It ruined my visit.

result.adr_address: 1457 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1457 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Pera

result.reviews.text: we had the hummus to start it was served warm with fresh baked pita so good, then we had the flaming cheese dish (yes! the cheese is the cracker the date is the spread!) the greek yogurt sauce cheese pasta with smoked garlic paprika drizzle (amazing) and the thin beef with zesty tomato sauce and greek yogurt (my favorite) you MUST go if you love turkish medi fusion!
Pera is such a nice restaurant.  From the decor, the table setting, the food and the service ... all was perfect. We will be back for sure .... a delight.

Love this place!! it's my go to on Potrero Hill. Authentic Mediteranian food.
Great service, I am vegan and they have great things for me to eat and also my friends that aren't.
Good prices, too!

Excellent service and really flavorful food! Had a flaming cheese appetizer, the birds nest, and moussaka. Everything was delicious. We also followed up with the apricot dessert which was very tasty

Was this review …?
Delightful service, and wonderful Mediterranean cuisine. The Iskender, Ali Nazik, and Manti are great. Good for dinner.

result.adr_address: 1453 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1453 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Mac Daddy

result.reviews.text:
A newer spot in SF. There aren't many places to sit (a counter top, a few tables and some outside). 

The food is bomb and service good. They sell beer here so you can sip on a beer while you eat your delicious mac n cheese! It's a little hard to spot from the street though.
Fantastic Mac and cheese. Gluten free pasta available. Reasonably priced. Small place, though, so I wouldn't recommend this for big groups. Great date place.
The tastes are amazing. I've only had the Mac and cheese but I'm sure the rest is great too. Place in small but the food makes it worth great. Great for to go orders. A bit pricey though.
Great quality food cooked right in front of you, reasonably priced and a great vintage feel. Only downside was having to walk through the kitchen to use the bathroom and no wi-fi.

The food is very good, and the staff is super friendly. 4 starts because it's a bit pricey ... But portions are big. Personally, I wish they had a smaller/cheaper option. 

I'd definitely go check it out!

result.adr_address: 1434 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1434 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Aperto

result.reviews.text:
People here are very nice.
The place is very tiny and simple but cozy.
Good food, rotating specials and no wait! (Saturday at 1:00 pm)

We were staying in the neighborhood and ate at a number of restaurants on 18th. We had the pasta special spaghetti with clams.  It was very good, lots of seafood and great flavor. The service was friendly and attentive. The place was busy and the atmosphere was energetic but not boisterous - just right. The decor was typical of generic Italian restaurants. When we were there, someone came in to pick up a large take-out order and the staff were very helpful in assisting her to get into her vehicle. That kind of speaks to the service in here. They do more than go through the paces.
Really small place with a small but diverse menu. We made reservations (about and hour ahead of time) and it was pretty busy.  We'd definitely go back. Service and food were both excellent.

Aperto is the quintessential neighborhood Italian restaurant. The ambiance, dishes, and service is a wonderful blend of pre-tech boom 2.0 city charm with the old country sensibilities. I always leave here satiated, and grinning from ear to ear. 

**Dishes that make me go MmmmmYUMmmm: 
Handcrafted Burrata, Mushroom Polenta, Tagliolini Pepati, all of their linguini specials, Seared Tombo Tuna

As young adults coming into this restaurant, we felt judged from the moment we walked in. We aren't 15, you don't need to forejudge us before we've even sat down. We even got reservations. We were polite and courteous and impressed with the vibe of the restaurant from the moment when we walked in- yet we still felt silently judged - as if we 'couldn't afford to be here' or not welcome. Overall, a very pretentious and judgmental environment for young people.
Please be more welcoming towards all customers, and would love if the waiters smiled more! Look like you love your job! Have fun, so we can too! I shouldn't feel ashamed to laugh and have a nice time in your restaurant. We drove 15 hours to come to San Francisco, and invest in a nice dinner. 
Let us enjoy ourselves. (The man with the black man bun and facial hair had a welcoming energy and a nice vibe. Funny and nice. He served us cheese. Nice guy. Too bad he wasn't our waiter.)
When we were offered a beverage, our server invited us to some sparkling water- which ended up being $6 without our consent for this purchase. Please be more clear with your marketing.
The food was excellent. All the vegetarian options tasted great. 5/5 food.
Portions were well done and filling. Fresh and elegant.
Honestly, wouldn't come here again without a Groupon due to the environment, until I'm at least 30 when I'll be able to dine here without feeling like I'm being judged. If you are looking for a nice place for you and your adult friends to dine, this is a nice place.
Thanks for the memory, Aperto!

result.adr_address: 1415 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1415 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Provender Coffee & Food

result.reviews.text: My first visit to Provender was awesome. The staff was very friendly and the coffee was delicious. I also had a piece of black sesame banana bread that was very tasty. Highly recommend this place!
Everyone is so friendly and the atmosphere is perfect for a small neighborhood coffee bar.  My favorite!!!
Andytown coffee, homemade baked goods, friendly staff! Very solid!
Eclectic selection of fresh-made quality food to go, teas, and really good coffee
Great spot with sight glass coffee. I would say it's $$, not $ though.

result.adr_address: 1401 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1401 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Chez Maman

result.reviews.text: Lovely brunch place. Very crowded moody of the time but they seat you relatively quickly. I had the spicy sausage sandwich with melted brie and it was great
Simply incredible. Staff is super on point. Food I awesome. GelatI was great. Just go

Superb service. Limited seating. Food needed a little salt, crepe was a bit pricey and bland. 4 - 5 stars for service. (3 stars for food)

Everyone here actually speaks French!
Great atmosphere, incredible food and friendly service! Also, some of the best ice tea I've ever had.
Great steak frites, burgers, mussels, fish, French onion soup, chicken, and truly great fries.  Creme brulee.  Sexy waiters.

result.adr_address: 1401 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107-2801, USA
result.formatted_address: 1401 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Chez Maman

result.reviews.text: We were staying in the neighborhood and went to a number of the establishments along 18th Street. This place definitely exudes a french atmosphere. I had the veal as well. It was good but the meat was not as tender as I would have expected and it was on the salty side and lacking a bit in flavor. The service was friendly and attentive. The place was quite busy and had an energetic atmosphere.
Good service, delicious food, relaxed atmosphere.
Typical French cuisine, high quality food! I would definitely go back next time I am is SF!
The service is spot on. Everyone is French and super friendly!
I love Chez Maman.  It's such a cozy little space and the food is incredible.  I almost always order mussels but literally everything I've had on the menu here is good.  I definitely recommend.

result.adr_address: 1319 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107-2822, USA
result.formatted_address: 1319 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Hazel's Kitchen

result.reviews.text: Love love love Hazels. Great sandwiches and wonderful friendly service. The breakfast sandwiches are delish.
Great little neighborhood spot for a quick breakfast or lunch. Hole in the wall but effectively operates as a collective with Farley's next door.

Really tasty breakfast sammies on fresh bagels. Great for a quick and less expensive option in Potrero Hill. Grab a coffee from Farley's and a breakfast sandwich or burrito for an under-$10 start to your day!
Amazing sandwiches. Also their soup is delicious. Good options for vegetarians. The breakfast menu is great as well. And to top it, the people are amazing. Would highly recommend this place
Best Grilled Chicken Pesto sammie around Portrero Hill.  A must try!

result.adr_address: 1328 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1328 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Umi

result.reviews.text: Great sushi at a decent price. Always fresh. The fatty sardine is a personal favorite. They have a fantastic sake menu, too.
This place is amazing! Fish is fresh, all food is ridiculously tasty and the staff is awesome!
Great little sushi joint in Potrero, rolls run $12-16. Nice sake selection to choose from.
Fantastic sushi, great service. Loved the halibut cucumber salad!

A great sushi spot in Potrero.  With the other option being Live Sushi (or Whole Foods too if you count that), Umi is definitely the better option in my opinion.  The fish is fresher which makes all the difference.  I like the sashimi combinations, which also come with rice and miso soup.

result.adr_address: 1299 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1299 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Plow

result.reviews.text: If you are a brunch lover, this is the place to go. Incredible food, that's definitely worth the wait. I usually judge brunch places by their Eggs Benedict and Plow's version was one of the best I've had. They included crispy potatoes on the side that were to die for. I also recommend getting their seasonal chia pudding, which is creamy and delicious and served with local fruit on top.

Happened to stay 1 block away.
Very convenient for us because we can drop by during weekday or before the crowd arrive.

The brunch has a very rustic feel. Love the potatoes.

Try the Corn beef hash.

My absolute favorite brunch spot in the city! Expect to wait in line for a seat, and bring warm cloths in case you get seated outside.
I recommend trying the potatoes, they are excellent!

Truly delicious brunch that will fill you up and leave you wanting to come back for more. The interesting flavor twists on brunch classics like the french toast with blood orange vanilla bean compote, the lemon ricotta pancakes, and the chicken apple sausage make the Plow menu unique and worth going out of your way to try. Every menu option, down to the scrambled eggs (which come with shitake mushrooms, nettles, and goat cheese) is given special attention to ensure it is not what you would find in another restaurant. Regardless of what you get, make sure you save some room for the delicious plow potatoes, which are like a twist on hash browns and compliment just about any sweet or savory flavor.

Just plan to take family, friends or recomend visitors. It is true, you have to wait in line but, it is worth to seat hungry in this place. I order The Plow: eggs, bacon, pancakes and potatoes were cooked to perfection. This place should be in TV. Inertview people before they eat and interview after  eating. Please, eat here with confidents. Enjoy 🤖.

result.adr_address: 1717 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.formatted_address: 1717 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Twirl and Dip

result.reviews.text: Great place for soft ice cream. They have the usual chocolate and vanilla flavours, but I've also seen that they sometimes have mint, ginger, and strawberry. And sometimes twists of two flavours :) I haven't tried the hard ice cream here (Mitchells) or the dipped fruit, but my friend always gets the banana dipped in chocolate and seems to enjoy it. You can also get the ice cream dipped in chocolate with some salt, if you'd like. I tried it once. It was good, but I got tired of the mix of flavours after a while since the portions are pretty sizable, and I just get the usual chocolate/vanilla twist (no dipped chocolate and salt) since then.
Best soft serve in the bay area period!  You can tell they care about every ingredient.  I will go out of my way to stop here.

I called asking where they're ice cream truck goes to and I let her know that I live in a different state and she rudely accused me of wasting her time when in fact I am planning a trip to the golden gate park area.  Horrible people!!

Tucked in a little alley off of 17th St, the shop is spartan, but it is right next to Jackson Playground. They had four flavors of house-made soft servce - it was tasty, but seemed priced too high at $4. They also had several flavors of Mitchell's ice cream. The staff was quite friendly.
I know it's a soft serve place, but I love that they have Mitchell's here.  Especially the grasshopper pie.

result.adr_address: 1435 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1435 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: JB's Place

result.reviews.text: Good food good prices. Love the people who work here - they are very nice. Serves amazing breakfast and lunch.
This place rocks. Super fresh (had deli sando) and fast. Thanks guys!
Really nice place. Great food, nice people. I've had my employees going there for years. They all love JB's!
Best quick breakfast in the area

Simple, classic neighborhood lunch spot with no-nonsense service and a surprising amount of seating, both indoor and outdoor.  The gyro platter is delicious and the pulled pork sandwich is even better, though their "hot food" buffet is less compelling.

result.adr_address: 100 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107-2415, USA
result.formatted_address: 100 Connecticut St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: The Connecticut Yankee

result.reviews.text: A local joint that shows all Red Sox and Patriots games in addition to local teams. I come here regularly and never have the service issue noted. In fact the food always comes out quick and I've only had a couple misses. Favorite is definitely the Bim Bap Burger.

Nothing special about this place. Typical divey pub. One bar tender was a total jerk to us when we visited a few months ago. We're regulars since we attend grad school nearby, and they never bother to remember or recognize us. Food is pub food but better than I expected. I only go here because there aren't enough other options around.

The Third bar of the "Pour Guys", the CY is a lovely balance between Louie's down town swank crowd and the Tempest dive vibe.  A lovely spot for a neighborhood meal out on the patio, or watching a game at the bar.  Also, I think their pool table is one of the better bar tables around..

Local dive bar. We walked in and weren't acknowledged for probably 5 minutes. The only waitress there ignored us. Sunday night and only a handful of people there; mostly empty. We waited at the bar and after waiting some more, the bartender finally acknowledges us and we order from him.
We ordered the popcorn shrimp and cod, the guac plate and beer. The food we got was uninspired and desperately overpriced. Tiny bowl of shrimp with 6 super mini wedges of lemons, and flavored ketchup and mayo for $15. The guac was good but also over priced for $13 and a very little amount of food. For $28, I left still hungry.

They do have a good selection of local brews. I'd come here for the beer, not the food or service. Would probably not come back, ever.

Decent dive bar. Lots of space and lots of tvs for playing sports. I went there to meet some friends and I had no trouble getting an entire table for us to use. The staff was friendly and they recommended certain foods from the menu (though don't expect much more than generic bar food)

result.adr_address: 1135 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1135 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Ganims Market

result.reviews.text: Have you ever had a cheeseburger in a liquor store? You probably should. Don't worry, it's really quite tasty, and amazingly cheap.
Lots of choices. Good lamb gyro, burgers. Inexpensive.
Quick and easy spot to grab some lunch

Love coming here frequently because the owners are always friendly and kind. I have had their best burgers, fish and chips, and just last night had their chicken salad. Delicious. It had pineapple pieces that gave it a citrus taste, avocado, fresh cut lettuce and more. The chicken was grilled. Great service. A great place to eat, too when you're on your way to either the Giants or 49er game (well at least for this football season in the city). They do have a TV.

If you live in The City or The Bay Area and you have not eaten at this jewel, you are not a true local and know nothing about a cheeseburger. Bang for your buck burgers and other items. In And Out is your bar, keep eating there! I'll  be here. SFPD know where the flavor is as I usually see a crew eating there, too. Should be illegal to melt cheese like they do on that flat grill!

result.adr_address: 1600 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107-2332, USA
result.formatted_address: 1600 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Thee Parkside

result.reviews.text: Back courtyard is great as are burgers but otherwise this lackluster dive disappoints on service and expensive covers for unheard of bands with very little decor or other appeal. We go here often as grad school is close but they never remember us. Wish there were better options nearby.

The Interrupters played on Sunday and the show was great. The venue is on the small side (which is awesome to see your favorite bands), but hopefully something can be done about the ventilation. It was a sauna in there...a couple of fans should work to circulate the air flow. Just a suggestion :)
Cool ambiance and chill spot.  I like the outside patio!  The food was also yummy.

Great cash only establishment, just remember to deduct the ATM fees from your tip. I'm here often and love the patio, the food and the atmosphere. Staff is great and selections aren't only ipas, I like that.
Local dive with decent food. It felt a lot cooler before vapid 24-year-old startup kids working in Potrero started having their work team meetings there.

result.adr_address: 2001 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-5012, USA
result.formatted_address: 2001 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Live Sushi Bar

result.reviews.text:
Cute place, solid ambiance, mediocre food.

The place is small, cozy, and the service is pretty decent. The people are nice and it's a relaxing spot to catch up with a friend. Unfortunately, the food doesn't quite live up to the same standard. I came here most recently on a Tuesday evening around 6pm and shared some food with my aunt:

Crab Napoleon: 4-stars. This best dish of the evening. Layers of crab, avocado, salmon, and tuna with yuzu creamy sauce. Topped with tobiko. Served absolutely gorgeously in a little tower. Super fresh, a good mixture of textures and flavors. $15.95

Agedashi Tofu: 2-stars. Lightly fried tofu, served in some kind of sauce that had no flavor and left the tofu soggy. A large portion though, three big pieces. $7.50

Nemo: 3-stars. Seared salmon wrapped scallops with a garlic butter dipping sauce. This sauce was also incredibly light on flavor, and while the seared salmon was full of flavor, it completely covered the delicate scallops. It was impossible to taste them in the dish. $11.95

Bergschneider Roll. 4-stars. Unagi and avocado roll topped with salmon. A really large roll, full of umami flavors and topped with super fresh salmon. $14.95

Local tip: try the sake flights! Huge, strong pours of vastly different sakes that will introduce you to a whole new thing if it's your first foray into sake.

Overall, I probably won't run back for food, there are just too many great sushi spots in town. That said, I might stop in for happy hour to grab a sake tasting!

Amazing sushi. This place has some of the freshest and most delicious sushi I've ever had. It's a little pricy, a good meal per person is about $35-50. The service is good and there's a very lively mood there.
Very good from service to meal. Doesn't get more fresh than live Sushi.
Visiting from out of town on a Monday. Fast, friendly service. Had the King Salmon nigiri special, amazing.  Next time will try one of the live options

I came here on a whim.

It was dinner time on a Friday and it was packed! I was seated at the very end of the bar. It was super crowded.

I was basic and ordered a bento box. I was brought a seaweed salad that I didn't order. The food was good. Service was spotty since it was so busy. I didn't like being squished.

I would come back early to try some actual sashimi.

result.adr_address: 1233 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.formatted_address: 1233 17th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
result.name: Bottom of the Hill

result.reviews.text:
Love this place for catching small shows. It's very small and cozy. We also hosted a friend's engagement party here and it was amazing.

You can rent the space out on nights they aren't booked for a show for much less than you would pay if you were, say, trying to buy the place out in lieu of a concert. You just have to wait for the next months' calendar to come out and then pick a date they would normally be closed. This calls for super fast party planning, but it's worth it.
Small SF staple of a place to see bands. Very loud. Serve food and have a smoking area in the back. Cash only. ATM next to the front door.
Fine ales, excellent acts, low cover charge. Nice backyard patio zone. Wonderful punk rock crowd.

Love this venue... Sort of like if the Chain Reaction in Anaheim, CA and the Whisky-a-Go-Go in Hollywood,CA had a baby and sent it to live amongst the hippies of San Francisco. In your face intimacy (seriously it is house party close), an outdoors area, and a wicked upstairs "backstage" that I choose to remain mum on.

Good bands usually play here. If you traveling without a car, it might be a problem to walk here from 22nd street Caltrain station: the place is on the bottom of the hill, but you have to walk on the top of the hill before :).

result.adr_address: 1- USA, 99 Miles Ct, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 1- USA, 99 Miles Ct, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: John Steakhouse

result.adr_address: 905 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 905 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Aurea

result.reviews.text: Cute little place if your nearby on Nob Hill to grab a bite and a nice drink. Your eating in an extension of the hotel lobby in open air but this is such a cute hotel too it feels very cool to be here.

This review is only for Aurea, Stanford Court's restaurant. We went there for brunch with a Gilt City voucher and had a great experience! Parking is super hard in the area, but we valet parked at the hotel and they validated it in the restaurant. Our waiter was very helpful, when he overheard us talking about how hungry we are, brought us pastries before the food came. They have great bloody mary-s and you must try the corned beef hash, that was definitely one of their best dishes. The crab florentine, the mission scramble and the brioche french toast were very tasty as well.

All in all, I would definitely go back, the restaurant is in a nice area, you don't have to wait in line, and you can go to walk a little in the neighborhood after you stuffed your belly with yummy bites ;-)
One of my fave spots in the city. Amazing ambience, great food, and delicious wine

result.adr_address: 600 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 600 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Parallel 37

result.reviews.text: Simply special! Always can expect the great service from the Ritz and the prix menu was excellent wth flavors and selections that please. The chefs selection provides market fresh choices and when paired with wine a most tantalizing invigorating experience! Cost is worth the presentation and work that goes into the food.

The best all-around dinner value for your buck: rivals all the best restos with flavor, presentation, ambiance, casual service, without the pretention and hype. Portions are perfectly sized (3-course rather than a gazillion) with great wine selection and pairing, really an understated hidden gem in SF. Been here twice and 2 for 2 excellent meals and service so it is consistent. Lamb and pork loin was amazing, as was everything else. Super friendly down to earth staff, and noise factor was perfect. They truly deserve more notice.
Fantastic food. Great service. Lacks a bit of atmosphere.
Fantastic wine selection and excellent food - totally worth making a trip to Parallel 37.  Also, be sure to save room for dessert!

We came here for a late lunch once, and (while perfectly enjoyable) my feeling was that this is more of a dinner place. Lunch was served in a large, bright room outside the restaurant. The menu was quite limited, featuring only various essentials. I had the spaghetti pomodoro, which was pretty tasty. Service was very friendly. Nice spot if you want a quiet lunch away from the crowd.

result.adr_address: 600 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 600 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: The Lounge

result.reviews.text: Pretty good for a drink & a quick snack.

While the lobby lounge was elegantly decorated with harp music playing, the flavorless sandwiches made with stale bread were surprisingly disappointing. The selection of sweets was quite substantial, and the scones were tasty.  Moreover, the customer service was top-notch- when I provided feedback to the server and the manager (who came by our table), about the sandwiches, they immediately brought over a new plate of sandwiches made with a different bread that was a bit better tasting and took one of the tea service off the bill.

I must say I was surprised at how quiet the bar was.  Perhaps the fact that it was a Sunday evening had something to do with it.  I did receive excellent service from a friendly bar tender.  The selection of red wine was outstanding.

Simply fab! The newly remodeled Ritz brings together old world Ritz glamour with a modern feel. The lounge is great pre-or-post going out for a night on the town. Drinks are strong and tasty. The mood is sophisticated. I always meet interesting people here, so it's also a great place to sit at the bar and mingle with new friends from around the world.

that susi is teast good
and they have some special japanese food
and this place has very good looking

result.adr_address: 950 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 950 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Tonga Room & Hurricane Bar

result.reviews.text:
Drinks: I found all the drinks very sweet; both their special drinks and standard cocktails.

Ambiance/Space: loved it! There's a pool inside with rain that comes on from time to time. When I went, there was a live band playing on a boat in the pool which was loads of fun. They have a dance floor where people from all ages are dancing! They've got high tables for standing as well as normal tables to sit.

Entrance: there are two entrances; one from the main lobby of the hotel and the other is from the backside of the hotel.

The only reason there are any stars on this review is because of the awesome atmosphere. We went there for drinks and dinner and wound up with sugar and salt. The drinks were strong and sugary, which was tolerable... But the dinner was inedible, even to two weary and hungry travelers. Incredibly disappointed in the food and am now eating Jack in the Box, which is sadly superior.

This is the kind of place you bring a group of out-of-towners, local friends who claim this is "touristy," and / or foreigners (to watch for their facial expressions). If you love Tiki kitsch and love Disneyland's Enchanted Tiki Room show, this place is even better because it serves Asian fusion food, pupus and lots of foo foo fruity rum umbrella drinks. 

The live band comes in and out on a moving barge in the "lagoon" under a  periodic tropical rainstorm with thunder and lighting. 

Very much a party atmosphere. People are friendly at the bar (maybe because of the all the rum being served). Plenty of picture /selfie taking moments within all this Polynesian campyness.

Drinks are pricey (but it's not like you hang out here every night). Best bet is to uber because hotel parking is expensive! And trying to find parking in the Nob Hill is next to impossible.

If you are not from San Francisco (and I mean out of state or the country) it could be a fun place to go. Otherwise it is just another tourist trap. There is a swimming pool (wait is California still suffering of a severe drought?!) And stupidly expensive drinks. But you get crazy long straws and all drink from the same big cup. Great way to break boundaries!
Food was good, Service was phonaminal at every level. It rivaled any place Ive been anywhere in the U.S. including high end restaurants. Really was something special to find anymore.

result.adr_address: 999 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 999 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Top of the Mark

result.reviews.text: The view from this bar is stunning, the place is classy and serves good cocktails. Don't expect to eat so much or to have a proper dinner: you want to go there to enjoy your wine meanwhile you are looking at the sunset. Be ready to queue: it's not possible to reserve so usually the queue is long... But it's going to be worth

I brought my wife her for some drinks before dinner on her birthday. We returned after dinner for the live music, dancing and a few more drinks.  We had one of the best nights we ever had. Thank you to all of the staff members that made our night so great.
My grandfather enjoyed a drink here before heading off to war. Great views, great drinks. Wait can be long.

Good classic drinks, not much innovation. You pay for the view as the atmosphere is ok for a lounge. Not as upscale as the prices would lead you to believe. Nice place to impress out of towners who haven't experienced much of SF.

I went for a movie screening and bourbon tasting and the whole experience was fantastic. The dress code was very casual to slightly dressy (possibly just for this event). Drinks were of course expensive but they were incredibly delicious and perfectly strong.    You are paying for the view when you go and it is breathtaking. I definitely recommend going while it's light out and watching the sun as it sets.

result.adr_address: 950 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 950 Mason St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Laurel Court Restaurant & Bar

result.reviews.text: That was the worse $46 rib eye I ever ate.   It came alone without a salad veggies or potatoes.   Go get a pizza or anything else besides here.   How does this hotel rip off their customers with this dog food.   Also the view from our room was the water tank view.   Our room had no bureau to put your clothes in.   It is misrepresenting to the point of highway robbery.   GO Any place else.   Eat anyplace else.    Stay any place else.

Wonderful service that was welcoming and polite, but not overbearing. The grilled tuna and filet mignon were superb- the flavor was rich and bold! I would definitely go back if given the opportunity and will gladly recommend this dining experience to others.

Had the bagel breakfast sandwich with truffle brie and house potatos. Everything was cooked to perfection. The service was superb.  Servers were there only when needed, after that we were able to have a conversation without being interrupted. The ambiance was worth the visit. Well done.

Excellent restaurant for high tea time! Service is impeccable and very courteous. The spread was delicious and worth the higher than average cost. Teas are actually delicious (you'd be surprised how many high tea rooms don't put any emphasis on this). Beautiful restaurant to top it off!

Went here for breakfast.  Overpriced with average service and low quality food.  Oscar Meyer has better bacon.  Buffet is a ripoff.

Honestly,  this place is scenic,  and that's it.   Spend your money elsewhere.

result.adr_address: 815 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108-2120, USA
result.formatted_address: 815 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: New Fortune Dim Sum&Cafe

result.reviews.text: Good variety for a quick dim sum breakfast. You can sit down and eat or take it away. The prices are pretty cheap and you get the food right away.
I thought it was delicious cheap and filling. The noodles with spare ribs was sublime. Nothing fancy but the food is excellent. They do run out of certain items. Definitely try it!!
Amazing place. I love spare ribs and noodles for breakfast!
The shrimp dim sum was amazing! My husband and our two kids had a wonderful dumpling breakfast for $16 total and walked out with leftovers!! Very authentic - will go again.
Great food at a low price. I'm a regular customer. Friendly people.

result.adr_address: 1 Pagoda Pl, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 1 Pagoda Pl, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Hang Ah Dim Sum Tea House

result.reviews.text:
Loved it.
Unassuming exterior, and interior, but you're there for the food and the dim sum was delicious!
Friendly, informative, and patient service.

Wow!  This is the best dim sum I've had in my life!  Everything I tried was absolutely delicious.  Siu Mai, shrimp dumplings, pan fried pork buns, curry pot stickers, sticky rice with chicken, and the house tea of course.  They make the chili sauce in house & it's perfect.  Jumping to the top of my favorites list!
Great cozy place for dimsum. Xiao long bao little thick but overall good dumplings. Shumai is excellent. Everything is really hot so careful!
Family run restaurant, owner is very nice. Had the shrimp dumplings, mongolian beef, fried rice, and the sweet and sour pork chops. Everything was really tasty, spicy sauce is awesome.
Excellent food, amazing chili sauce and great service! Definitely eating here again before we leave.

result.adr_address: 700 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 700 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: 엉클비토 피자

result.adr_address: 724 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 724 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: BeanStalk Cafe

result.reviews.text: So nice bagel with super nice cheese and soft scrambled egg. Girls are really busy but kind! Enjoy
Tiny cafe with only a handful of seats but with an awesome menu of food and coffee choices. The spicy chicken sandwich was great, and the mocha was deliciously chocolatey.

Hole in the wall cafe spot and not too fast of a turn time for scrumptious bakery goods to come out of their oven. I wanted to try their toasted cups, but they said they ran out. I ordered their mint mojito coffee and they ran out of mint. Limited supply for a small cafe storage I suppose, to function. Few seatings and not the ideal bring-your-stuff to do work here for awhile cafe. I prefer that cafe vibe. The norm on coffee and sandwich menu. I left unimpressed.
Fabulous coffee and nice bagels (not overly toasted, plenty of cream cheese). My husband had the bagel sando with sausage and loved it :)

Really good sandwiches. For most locals the prices are normal, but for someone who's not used to paying 10 bucks for a sandwich, this may be a bit pricy.

Try the Spicy Chicken w/a little extra spicy sauce, its not hot, but has a nice kick to it. 

They do run out of some items. While this is a bit of an annoyance, they only make a certain amount of food and once it runs out, it runs out.  They are very conscious about this. If they run out at 3, try getting there by 2 or 1... That's what most of us do :) especially if you like the way they make their food.

result.adr_address: Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Sons & Daughters

result.reviews.text: My wife and I came here to celebrate our wedding anniversary. We picked the tasting menu and really enjoyed the food. The chefs paid close attention to the plating and really made us feel welcome.

To start, the service was incredible.  I went for my birthday, and each member of the staff wished me a happy birthday.  The menus were printed for me especially with my name on them again wishing me a happy birthday.  The service was attentive, but not there too frequently allowing for conversation.

Each course was creative and better than the last growing the meal throughout.  Awkwardly, one of my favorite parts of the meal was the bread courses between each of the savory dishes.

As the meal was coming to a close we ordered tea and then had a great talk with the server about teas in San Francisco, all of the teas at sons and daughters is provided by a local tea shop, Red Blossom.
Delicious food - with lots of miniplates between the main courses. Top notch service.
The food presentation is very nice and thought out. Their vegetables are very tasty and unique, however their meats are somewhat lacking.
cozy and intimate place with great food.  Made some great recommendations of dishes to try and service was good.  Can't wait to go back.

result.adr_address: 570 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94108-3835, USA
result.formatted_address: 570 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Roxanne Cafe

result.reviews.text: 'Zorba' salad was a great take on the traditional "Greek" salad.  I added grilled salmon and sliced avocado.  The salmon was grilled perfectly.  The avocado was ripe and a generous portion.

Food was OK and service also. But they add 17% service charge (tips) and they charge you with S.F.H.O tax, which is an employer contribution to the mandatory SF health coverage for restaurant workers (quote from TripAdvisor).

So the total price goes up by at least 30%.

Came to San Fran thinking I would get some great food, definitely picked the wrong place. The grilled Mahi never touched a grill and wasn't seasoned at all and the risotto was the equivalent of boil in a bag rice. Spent $65 for two then went up the street to get something edible.
Fantastic small cafe! Great staff and well prepared food. Try the Napa Omelet!

Great little spot for brunch and a Bloody Mary.  Friendly, engaging staff.  Had to sit at bar around 10am, but no wait.  Walked there, but Powell St cable car stop is right outside.

Not super fast on a Saturday morning, but we were not in a rush this morning.  Had the Corned Beef Sunrise.  Not normally a fan of Hollandaise sauce, but enjoyed this.  Wife had the Joey Special, which was good but liked the Corned Beef Sunrise better.

result.adr_address: 718 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108-2404, USA
result.formatted_address: 718 California St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Cathay House

result.reviews.text: We love it here!   Great bar atmosphere and strong drinks.   Also the occasional complimentary appetizer.   Last night it was sauteed oysters which were excellent.  Also chicken wings which we did not sample.

Bad choice.  Should have checked review before walked in.  Lousy food. Bad service.  Expensive pricing.  Wanton soup had no wanton filling, just skin and pathetic pieces of vegetable.  Ordered a noodle and was told that noodle stock had not been delivered by supplier (what a joke:-). Other dishes were saltish and tasteless.  Worst chinese restaurant ever been.
Rude service staff. Don't be taken by the location and exterior. I would give a 0 star if I could.

I've never been here and probably never will. So I dunno about the food. What I do know is that Michael Knight gave chase in KITT straight past this restaurant. It's even got the same red and gold banner up front in 2016 it had in 1985. So it can't be too bad, considering it survived for so long. And straight out of a Knight Rider episode. Looking out the window, you can almost see KITT drive past. Haha.

Agree with the other reviews. Worst experience - the food was really bad, even my 13 year old who loves Chinese food didn't want to eat his sesame chicken after a couple of bites. The waiter's jacket was so dirty that made things worse. Tips himself to top it all off 20%  Why is this place in business?
Very Bad service with bad food. Waiter spilled the food all over our table without saying sorry. The food was cheap and tasted like it was cheap too. I don't recommend this place at all.

result.adr_address: 631 Grant Ave, San Francisco, CA 94108-2401, USA
result.formatted_address: 631 Grant Ave, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: 康年海鲜酒家

result.adr_address: 888 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 888 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Cafe Honolulu

result.reviews.text: A truly old-school Hong Kong style cafe that had awesome milk tea sweetened with condensed milk. I recommend getting it half sweetened so you can really taste the black tea. I ordered the set breakfast which came with ham & macaroni in chicken broth along with a breakfast roll. It was good considering that it only cost me $5 for all the food.
I love this place in a hardcore foodie and I appreciate authenticity this place delivers. I will go here every time  I'm in town.
Love this spot. Off the menu I recommend the baked beef with egg. When I'm in a rush I always stop for a steamed bun usually before work. The small ones are only 65 cents

DONT EVER GO HERE! THE SERVICE SUCKS AND THEY BASICALLY THREW MY CHANGE AT ME AND WHEN I SAID THAT THEY NEEDED BETTER SERVICE, SHE IGNORED ME AND THE CASHIER WAS JUST MUGGING THE WHOLE TIME. THE FOOD WAS NOT EVEN GOOD IT WAS EITHER TOO PLAIN OR TOO SALTY JUST LIKE THEIR ATTITUDE. WORST WORST ABSOLUTE WORST PLACE EVER

Saw the pork buns from the window and we had to stop in.  Grabbed pork buns and sesame red bean balls, my guilty pleasure.  Both were amazing.  Didn't order off the menu.  The bakery items were solid and the perfect walking food for the China town hike.

result.adr_address: Tunnel Top Lounge and Bar, 601 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: Tunnel Top Lounge and Bar, 601 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Tunnel Top Lounge and Bar

result.adr_address: 665 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 665 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Daffodil Restaurant

result.reviews.text: This location has closed. Website confirms.

result.adr_address: 550 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.formatted_address: 550 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Last Drop Tavern

result.reviews.text:
I went here hoping for the food to be on par with that of the prior restaurant at the location - El Sotano Grill - but alas things didn't quite pan out that way.

Got the chicken street tacos.  Flavor wasn't bad, but was a bit light on the advertised cilantro (3 individual leaves don't do much).  Green salsa had some good heat, pico wasn't bad.

I asked for Chips and Salsa, was asked if I wanted Guac too (which I declined) and yet an $8 charge showed up on the bill for the Guac.  I was too tired after a long conference week to argue/inquire, so just let it be.

Decor was nice, service was OK.
Stumbled on this place a few weeks ago. Been back twice. I really like the atmosphere. Have been there on Sundays, mostly. Not too crowded. Good drinks good snacks.
Poor food and even worse was the service. Never again. Every Mc Donalds will serve you better

I love this place. It's near Union Square but just far enough away from the crowds to make this a nice spot to hang out, few grab drinks and eat some yummy food. They have food and drinks on the happy hour menu which is a huge plus. The staff are very friendly and make sure your drinks are always full.

Crowded as heck but that's how this bar was meant to be. Took a long time to get service (just for water, even) but we eventually got some drinks in and food, to boot. Prices were decent and the beer selection wasn't the biggest, but it pleased my ever-changing palate. Favorite: the Cheese Quesadilla.

result.adr_address: 715 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108-3402, USA
result.formatted_address: 715 Bush St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
result.name: Restaurant Jeanne D'Arc

result.reviews.text: A gem. Wonderful old decorations on the wall, Sara Bernhart as Joan of Arc and reproductions of famous medieval scenes. A very typical French staff reminds one of rive gauche. On Saturday a great wandering violinist. The $48 menu compris is better food at half the price of other places. Fabulous fresh soup, choice of starters and entrees (rack of lamb recommended) and several deserts hard to beat the souflée with grand marnier. Good moderately priced wine list. Usually can get in without reservation, particularly early in the evening and most weekdays.

We each had a lovely $48 prix fixe meal at Jeanne D'Arc in the Hotel Cornell.
We all started with a pureed veggie soup served with iconic sourdough bread and foil-wrapped (?) butter; I then chose the shrimp salad, lamb shank with gratin potatoes and haricots vert, and a raspberry-blueberry tart for dessert, then decaf coffee. My companions had spinach salads, duck confit, and Grand Marniere souflees. They were also delighted.

Portions were very satisfactory; I took home half the shank.
The meal was timed well and all dishes were expertly prepared and plated.
There is an elevator or stairs down to the underground eatery decorated with frescoes and antiques. Absolutely lovely.

Went for my Birthday celebration and both my mom and I enjoyed our dinner ...
If you want a taste of Paris and cant afford to run away....
This is a nice place that offers true taste of France.

Sweet place, cute if kitschy decor; classic French music, reminds me of a Bastille Day village fair.  Solid food, very French, served in a business-like French fashion.  Wine list by the glass is a bit mediocre, I had a half-bottle of St Emilion which was ok not great.  Otherwise classic, reliable, not necessarily exceptional cuisine -- and of course, finish with the soufflé!

Just a fantastic meal. This is a funny but beautiful place. Went on a Wed night. The waiter who probably has worked there for 30 years was the only server graciously served the 25 or so patrons who were there in my 1 1/2 or so time there. Prix fixe menu with a surprisingly long list of entrees for such a small place. I had a wonderful duck meal. Several wonderful desserts to choose from. And ridiculously inexpensive for what you get.

result.adr_address: 2031 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109-2519, USA
result.formatted_address: 2031 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Tai Chi

result.reviews.text: Warning: do not get their Shanghai dumplings and tiramisu.  You can get better dumplings at Chinatown for half the price. As for tiramisu, it's the worst ever! I have eaten many, and this is the only one that I couldn't finish.
Great food! Price and gentleness of service is really hard to beat
My neighborhood spot for take away. Staff are always nice, plenty of veggie options! I usually order the Kung Pao Tofu & Mixed Veggies.
Been going here for 20 years. The food is great. Only place I know that all the dishes can be ordered with gluten free option.
Consistently good! Can't get better than that!

result.adr_address: 2065 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2065 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Lord Stanley

result.reviews.text: Seasonal ingredients with balanced touch. We ordered tasting menu with paring wines and everything was perfect. We liked how they tried to bring out the ingredients' natural flavors. The Wagyu beef dish was little off balanced from the rest of the dishes. We all agreed that it was excessive.
One of my favorite restaurants in SF. Simple, beautiful food. Staff is amazing. Attentive and professional. Highly, highly recommend.
One of the new $ hipstery restaurants with good food and slow service.

Fun concepts translate to good eating. 

It took a while to be seated. Our table wasn't ready so they invited us to the bar. It's a tight fit in there - kind of awkward. 

Tasting menu was solid, but wish I could have replaced the wagyu with the short rib. 

Go on date night. Not a place for groups. 

Overall, this was a great experience.
We ordered the pre fix menu. I'd probably pass on the fois gras. The food and presentation were great. I liked free truffles they gave us at the end.

result.adr_address: 2035 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2035 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Country Sky

result.reviews.text: The food was good.  Delivery took 1 hour 20 minutes- a little long.  No forks or chopsticks were included (we are in a hotel).  They forgot an order of dim sum, and when I called to ask for my $6 back, they politely insisted that they included it in the bag - repeatedly.  It seemed like when she  hung up on me that it may have been an accident...but she never called back.  We may have just been unlucky tonight, but we were quite frustrated with this dinner experience.

I placed an order at 6p. I called at 7:35 to check on the order.  I was asked to hold, the phone was put down and I heard background noise for 7 minutes before I was hung up on. I called back and was told the food was ready and would be picked up to deliver soon. Since it wasn't even en route yet, I asked them to cancel the order, The woman convinced me it was leaving at that moment and would arrive soon. I said I would like a refund if it did not arrive by 8pm. TBD when it will get here. We've ordered from them before, and the food is good but the last time we ordered, they put a duplicate charge on our credit card. I don't think I'll be ordering from them again. I can't even find the restaurant on yelp to leave a review there.
Good food, nice staff, good price and quality and quantity.
Really tasty food at a more than reasonable price.  Probably one of the best Chinese restaurants I have ever been. The service is also fast, which is a plus.

This is a wonderful hidden little Chinese restaurant. Don't be shocked by the size...it seats 22 diners. The food is some of the best Chinese we have eaten. We are in San Francisco for three nights and just had our second dinner here. Try the sweet and sour pork! Outstanding. You will not be disappointed with any choice.

result.adr_address: 2100 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109-2511, USA
result.formatted_address: 2100 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Harris' The San Francisco Steakhouse

result.reviews.text: This place was just what we needed after flying all day.  The diligence of the staff and classic ambiance accentuated a very flavorful meal.   I had the New York strip steak in a peppercorn brandy sauce with grilled onions; the Mrs had the Diane style filet with a Demi glace on it.  As the beef was dry aged, it was very tender and also was cooked to perfection. Great light jazz band playing in the background too.

Kobe steak by the band is a must.
The steak is pricey...but so worth it.
Likely the best steakhouse in
my mind. Take a taxi from your 
hotel & skip your hotel eats.

Good steak but not prepared very well. Black and blue doesn't mean bitter. A common mistake of many steakhouses is overcooking the steak and this steak was cooked a bit too much, actually singed and the center needs to be cool. A piece of rosemary in the plate? Too outdated. Staff was friendly. Not coming back.
I order a rybee medium rare. It was cold, I told the captain who took te plate and in five minutes it arrives well done. Nobody said sorry. Horrible

NOISY AS HELL! 
We got a room upstairs.  By mind reflex it should've been intimate.
But it was noisier than the  cheapest bodega we have ever been before.  It cut any conversations that deep even the server was not able to get the correct order!!!

result.adr_address: 2050 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2050 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Hex To Go - Chinese & Thai

result.adr_address: 1500 Broadway, San Francisco, CA 94109-2516, USA
result.formatted_address: 1500 Broadway, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Nick's Crispy Tacos

result.reviews.text: The tacos here are so perfect.  If you don't live near SF don't eat here, you will be obsessed with eating these tacos for the rest of your life and that will either lead you to a deep depression or cause you to uproot your life and move to the bay area.
Great place for taco Tuesday specials but I prefer top go when it's not crowded. Grab a red velvet booth, a cocktail, then order your tacos regular or nicks way. Must try.

The stupidly shaped tacos, the way all the filling gets squished to one side, so you have the option of having way too much filing or nothing at all. Its a taco ice cream cone. Not to mention they have the confounding  seperation of drinks and food (which they love to remind you of) so you have to order from two separate places which makes no sense at all.  I simply do not understand why people like this place

Excellent. My tacos were so good. Two filled me up well. However the rouge service and bartender was garbage. I honestly wish the two were separate. Rouge is too different and loud. Next time I will just do take out.

The WORST and most expensive Mexican food in the city. I live a block away and haven't been back in two years.  Try the quesadilla!  Be prepared to throw the $13 monstrosity straight in the garbage. Just terrible. Anyone who says differently is probably from Minnesota. I retch when someone eats this slop within 5 feet of me.

result.adr_address: 2109 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2109 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Escape From New York Pizza

result.reviews.text: My favorite Pizza in San Francisco.  There may be better options out there, but I return again and again to Escape from New York Pizza.  Thin crust NY style pies are all they serve.  The crust is top notch, and their selection, while not super extensive, should suit most people looking for a good slice or two.

Poor customer service.
July 14, 2016...I called them at 11:14 pm 46 minutes before their closing time to confirm or order potato garlic pizza.
And they said it's going to be ready in 10_15 mintes. the made me drive, But when i got there the say "we are not going to make pizza".
Awesome spot for anytime pizza & an amazing spot for pizza by the slice for this rideshare driver.  There is always parking within a couple hundred feet late at night.
One of the best slices I've had in SF yet

Not great, especially for east coast transplants or visitors. Pizza is flavorless and the crust is just not that appetizing. Poor excuse for New York style pizza. Slices are also small and expensive. There are better pizza choices in the city.

result.adr_address: 1998 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 1998 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Belcampo Meat Co.

result.reviews.text: I ordered a bloody double quick burger.  I got a well done, flavorless, plain burger.  Also, the Eclair french dip;  flavorless meat on a mushy brioche bun.  Don't believe the hype.Never again.  Fried were good.  I prefer Jack In The Box.

We've had brunch here on a few occasions. Their sausage and bacon quality are superb (as expected of a meat shop). We also adored their ricotta pancakes. Very reasonable prices and no wait at all. Why bother with Mymys when you have Belcampo :) also love that it is spacious and I dont have to sit 2 feet away from the next table like most sf brunch places.

a butcher shop that is a restaurant come here for happy hour a burger, fries and a beer for $15 pretty good deal for SF. I like the place but the vibe feels off trying to be a fancy steak place but when you enter you come through the butcher shop the quality is the meat is fantastic
Quality meat selection but it comes at a hefty price
Beautifully presented meaty meals that appeal to the conscientious omnivore.

result.adr_address: 2127 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2127 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: dakshin: A South Indian Canteen

result.reviews.text: I had the gunpowder dosa, and it came with lentil stew and chutneys like all the dosa dishes. There was spiciness in both the dosa and the stew that I loved, and in all the flavors are incredible. The staff were friendly, offering to explain the menu and showed me the different portion sizes.
Amazing south Indian food at a great price

result.adr_address: 2101 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109-2510, USA
result.formatted_address: 2101 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Happy Donuts

result.reviews.text:
Been in here twice now. Good food, good selection of items, and nice staff. 

P.S. They're not native English speakers, which is not the same as being uneducated.

Food it can be good , but they have a terrible customer service, this people have no education to treat the customer I had a wrong order one time and they did not want to deal with it.  
I came back and sat down for  breakfast with my family ,because I think the food can be good and this time the guy was rude because I wanted my small coffee in a medium cup and he demanded the 25 cents there on the spot I thought  it wasn't nice the way he ask for it and told him I want my money back and he denied it !!! at some point in the argument he said he was going  to give me the money back for the rest of the breakfast but then this woman from kitchen come and yelled at us saying no money back we left with a sloppy  sandwiches and had the worse time .
I will never go again here! So if you decide  to go make sure of your order because for sure there is no money back!
Service was fast, cashier was nice, fries are godly, nice place to sit and take a rest.
Huge array of donuts, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, etc; low prices. Very clean and bright store. Pretty basic but cheerful. Recommended :)
Great food!

result.adr_address: 2201 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109-2512, USA
result.formatted_address: 2201 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Peter D's Restaurant

result.reviews.text:
This place has a good amount of brunch options and interesting specials. The food was delicious and the staff was very polite. 
It's a great pick if you are looking for a good brunch place which is super busy.

The raisin bread French toast was quite good, the portions were generous, & the decor was set by an old-school retro charm that seems to be an unintentional vintage throwback to that era simplistic 70's 

 the service was top notch (especially since it came from the smiling face of the genuinely friendly & refreshingly unpretentious efforts of one just completely beautiful & absolutely downright completely--to the depth of her sturdy fu**ing core--SEXY--at least through the lenses of exponentially increasing intrigue that filtered my vision while she was in sight).
So slow that was such painful to waiting for everything here and the food wasn't great at all with expensive price. The Lori's Diner on 500 sutter street is much much better then this sh*t food.
Aweful food never eat there again waitress was cool

What looked like a reasonably priced breakfast became ridiculously expensive with all the extra added fees.  We paid extra because we ate after 11am.  We paid extra for chocolate chips added to the pancakes, etc.  Our family of 4 ended up with a $65 dollar bill for extremely average food.  Servings were small and we all left hungry and disappointed.

result.adr_address: 1958 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 1958 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Basik Cafe

result.reviews.text: Fresh fruit smoothies or frozen blends are almost the size of a meal. Great for proper fresh fruit fix, especially on a hot day. Watch out for restrictive business hours.

Don't let the lines on the weekend scare you, this place is worth every second of waiting. I can't imagine a more perfect way to start my day. The only thing that would make Basik better is if there were more locations all over the city!
Wow this place has the best acai bowls I've ever tried in the world. Inside is very clean and everything is arranged nicely.

This place is awesome, I  feel revitalize every time after a fresh bowl of delicious deliciousness at Basik Acai.   If your visiting San Fran, be sure to stop by for a bowl of Acai- my personal favorite the Banyan and Forager!

Real acai bowl🙀
I ordered puna
Non-daily, plant- based, superfood meal 👍🏻

result.adr_address: 2141 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2141 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Street Restaurant

result.reviews.text: Fabulous food.  We came here with a large group, and everyone got something different and loved what they had.  The meat balls were amazing.  Lamb burger delicious, although it could have used more in the way of toppings. Our service was great, the beer list covered all the basics.  The menu was simple, but the flavors complex.  Ambience was a little dim for early evening. Nothing bad to say.
This has been my favorite restaurant in San Francisco since it opened.  I have never had any item here that is less than delicious.
Had dinner there twice on our trip from Europe to San Francisco. Nice location, great atmosphere, tasty food. Prices are Ok.
Great food, good drinks selection, cool atmosphere
Great ribs! Chef John is amazing.

result.adr_address: 2157 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2157 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: House of Sushi

result.reviews.text: Amazing 🙌🏽.....chef Katsuya is amazing!!!  If you love sashimi I highly recommend the tuna/salmon sashimi platter. If you're feeling adventurous let Katsuya pick. If you're a nigori lover like I am, I recommend the Kikusui. This is a sushi house after all, so I cannot comment on their other dishes, but the sushi was grade A++.

Came here in a whim after a Giants game and it was awesome! Sushi was so fresh, we ordered the chef's choice platter and I couldn't have chosen a better selection myself. Seaweed salad was simple yet one of the best I've evwr had, and everything was so cheap! Skip the wait at the high end places with loud atmosphere, House of Sushi is a great stop for some delicious, simple, and authentic sushi
Great food. Fresh fish. Friendly owners and staff.
We ordered sushi to pick up, so I am not commenting on the people or the service but the food was pretty bad :(

Our neighbourhood favourite. Go here at least once-a-week. Chef is incredibly friendly and food is great at a very reasonable price. Dragon roll is my favourite roll. We usually get a big mix of sushi as it's all good. Cold, dry sake is usually a welcome addition

result.adr_address: 1900 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109-3006, USA
result.formatted_address: 1900 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Bell Tower

result.reviews.text: Had a delicious dinner at the Bell Tower -- fish tacos and potato skins to start and the pulled pork sandwich for my main. Fish tacos were my favourite with a good amount of tuna and a great sauce although the hard, flat tortilla made them a bit messy to eat. The staff was on the ball and accommodated my party to continue watching an NBA playoff game on a different TV when the Giants game conflicted.
Nice bar. I had the quesadilla which was OK. I might try again
Great food, great service!  Barbie is the best!
We had dinner and drinks here and both were very good. The service was by far the best we had from LA to San Francisco. Food was reasonable and service was without a doubt incredible.
Fantastic service along with excellent food, despite the fact the place was packed for game 1 of the finals. This team of servers most defenitely gets it. Will be back.

result.adr_address: 2001 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2001 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Subway

result.reviews.text: I live nearby, food is good during the day. I don't recommend late night. Service is usually good. Clean, but have never been in the restroom....

This place is much great!
The other day, I bought sandwich here but I dropped it on the floor right after. 
The clerk cleaned them up right away and made another one for free!
Nice people here.
Subs are Subway quality, staff is friendly. However, restroom without soap (dispenser defect, supposedly for longer), no paper, no soap replacement. Food + toilet fingers are no good match.
Its a subway. Staff was welcoming and made it "my way." Location was clean sandwich was predictable.
Went at 11 pm.  Bread was dry, tuna was dry.  Almost like it been out since dinner rush. May be the usual during the day but think twice later at nite.  Based on only one visit.

result.adr_address: 2164 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109-2507, USA
result.formatted_address: 2164 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Crave

result.reviews.text: The best chicken and smoked pork sandwiches we have had. Local microbrews. Espesso drinks and french press. Indoor seating for around 35. Friendly, helpful staff.
Fun place to get a beer and sit outside. Super friendly staff. Owner always has a smile on her face.
Friendly staff, good sandwiches, though a bit small for the price
Tasty food! Environment was a little overwhelming for me personally. There was a group of kids that were VERY kid-like.

Really love the sandwiches here.  I think that this place is great for a fast meal, but the sandwiches can be pretty pricey ($12).

The good thing is is that it's smack dab in the middle of Polk street and you're able to grab a quick bite to eat, and then go to the bars around the area to watch football games, etc. 

I would say come here if you want a fast and simplistic meal!

result.adr_address: 2299 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109-2512, USA
result.formatted_address: 2299 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Wasabi & Ginger

result.reviews.text:
My value go-to sashimi! It might not be thee best in town but tasty large cuts of fish at an affordable price for SF, for those who like to easy sashimi on the reg but not go broke.

I get their Sashimi Plater Regular which has 15 pieces mixed sushi (all the regulars) for $23 and includes complementary edamame. Their X-Roll is also excellent. For a step up hit Ace Wasabi and do their happy hour 20 piece platter for $20, but this only applies during 5:30pm-7pm M-F (otherwise grossly overpriced).
Great neighborhood spot. Quiet and cozy atmosphere. Chill place to go alone. Food is verrrrry niiiiiiiice.
Great quality food, definitely underrated since they are one block off of busy polk street, they don't see nearly as much foot traffic despite being the best sushi choice in the area.

I did not enjoy this sushi spot. The service was slow and the food was not good. The interior is a little run down as well. And for a place called Wasabi Ginger, we didn't get any wasabi or ginger with our sushi. I will not go back here.

If you are looking for a fancy, upscale sushi restaurant, this place is not for you. If you are looking for a no frills, neighborhood spot with great service and fresh fish, Wasabi and Ginger is the spot. My boyfriend and I had a craving for sushi, and wanted to avoid the pricey spots in the Marina. We headed to Wasabi and Ginger and took a seat at the bar, and we were attended to immediately. We started off with the Chef's Special, which had a great variety of options. The chefs behind the bar kept checking in with us, and any time we asked them for another order, they whipped it up in just minutes. We left with full bellies and smiles on our faces, and we only had to walk 2 blocks home! We will be back often!

result.adr_address: 2209 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2209 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: Bullitt

result.reviews.text:
I've had too many good times here to not give it 5-stars. 

It's an unassuming place, but always has good vibes. 

Always single people here on the hunt, and the bartenders seem to always be in on the fun. 

The vibe can be anywhere from pretty chill to WILD, just depends on the night and the volume of the music. 

They serve 40s of Old English in the bar!
Great food and friendly staff!! Small to medium eating area. Place packs up quick. Good atmosphere with 90's and early 2000's mix of hit music.
Great place when they allow folks to bartend on behalf of nonprofits. Otherwise a bit small, dark, and loud (which if that's your thing, great place!).
My gem on Polk street. $0.25 cent wing Wednesdays (they bake the wings and are amazing). It tends to get busy around 6pm until the late hours but friendly staff and good prices!
5 stars for $5 Monday dinner menus. Best value on Polk

result.adr_address: 2227 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.formatted_address: 2227 Polk St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
result.name: House Rules

result.reviews.text: 5 stars for the bar - nice bar, good atmosphere and good choice of drinks. 1 star for the moody female bartender. We appreciate tipping in the US might be different than it is the UK, but prompting my boyfriend and I not to forget to tip before we'd even left is not good etiquette. Always happy to leave a good tip for good service. Not so much for people who don't smile, aren't that helpful and ask in advance for a tip.

Great neighborhood sports bar with good food. It's a bit classier than the normal sports bars on Polk Street. You won't feel weird drinking wine here.
Also the service is great. There's a backroom thats good for a small group.
I recommend the fried chicken and their cocktail or wines. Oh also lots of TVS, but the bar is small and can feel narrow at times. Definitely coming back.

New spot on polk street that offers small bites and a nice selection of beers and spirits. Formerly the spot that housed Pesce and Uno Dos Tacos, it another nice nieghborhood spot in Russian Hill. You can't go wrong with the food program set up by Scott Youkilis of Hog and Rocks. I tried the potato skins and meatballs and weren't disappointed. My rye manhattan was on point too.
If you like bullit you'll like this.
I love this place.  Drinks are great, food is great, staff is great!  Must come by if in the neighborhood

Good food. And taste great. I love it.

result.formatted_address: 3364 26th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Rincon Peruano

result.reviews.text: The best homestyle Peruvian restaurant in the city! I probably go here once a week because the food is so good. I love the Pescado frito and lomo saltado. The price is a bit steep for the neighborhood ($15-$17/plate) but the food is so worth it! You also need to order the alfajores. I've had alfajores from Argentina and they weren't this good. It has a great balance of sweetness and stickiness in the caramel and the short bread isn't hard - just right. Definitely recommend checking this place out.

Small cash-only hole in the wall away from Mission St with 4/5 big tables. The pescado frito is good, the lomo saltado is really good. Most dishes are $13 and the lomo saltado is $15 for lunch-size portions. I miss Inkas @ Mission/29th St where you could get a lunch special with soup, lomo saltado and a drink for $12. So it is worth going back to Rincon Peruano for the food, but at that price point you have many other options.

Love teh Bistek and Pescado Frito!  I've been eating at this place for about a decade.  If you are looking for fancy and ambiance this is not the place for you.  If you are looking for some authentic no frills but excellent food this is the place.
Exquisito el estofado de pollo y el tradicional aguadito de pollo.
DONT WAIST YOUR MONEY.!!!!!!!

result.reviews.text: Good end exelend pupusas the Realpupusas
Great little shop. The papusas are amazing. They also do a little but of everything here!
solid breakfast burrito, very fair prices

Family run fast service food spot. Great Breakfast Burrito.  Also nice Latino bfast plates like blk beans, huevos, and queso!  Very friendly mom and daughter run the show in the am.  I've never been at lunch.  Closes on the early side.   Great spot for people visiting the Balmy St murals.
Super authentic tasty. Worth the wait for the hand patted delights.
