result.name: Dum - Indian Soul Food

result.reviews.text: Dahi puri And kathi rolls and biryani were all great, excellent addition to the Mission!

Had the samosa chaat, pork Kati roll, veg paratha and chicken skewers. All were great but the Kati roll was my favourite. Service was great, the chef also gave us a free taster of the dahi puri and was really friendly.  That plus 2 beers and the bill came to $40 which I felt was very reasonable.  We will be back
Lamb biryani was very tasty. I noticed their seasonal Lasso was "Pumpkin Spice"- I'll definitely have to try next time I'm in.
Best/only Dhai puri in the mission. Skewers are amazing as well
Recently opened, i had "byriani" that was fresh, hot and very savory with some sort of bean-based side dish. Notably good spices. Costs just a little more than a neighborhood burrito.

Authentic Nicaraguan food in the heart of the historically Latin Mission District of San Francisco
Oxtail soup is delicious!!!

result.adr_address: 2937 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.formatted_address: 2937 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Evil Eye

result.reviews.text: Was just wandering when we stumbled upon the illuminati!  Great ambience/decor inside.  Restroom (individual type) was superbly maintained it is insane.  The way the seats are arranged was perfect whether you need to share with others or by yourself.  Level of illumination was also just right and the place wasn't loud, so it is conducive for conversation.  What a gem in the Mission district.

WELL, this bar is amazing. You spend as much time pouring over the décor as you do the menu. Both gorgeous! The Sweet Petunia and the Drunken Sailor are go-to drinks, hands down. Bonus-they come in vintage glassware that is so on point that, honestly, you are just upset that you don't own it personally. Warm/cozy/inviting atmosphere. One stop bar for a group/a few/solo. Creative bartenders, wonderful staff. Worth a trip out to the mission just for this!

Good creative drinks, and delicious bar bites with a nice lounge-like atmosphere.

They kept the gorgeous bar that was there before but got rid of the stage for seating and tables, making a laid-back feel.

LOVE LOVE LOVE the couches!! After an early Rise & Shine, this is just the spot to really unwind, whether you're in a group or would like to spend some one-on-one time with that "sparkle" in your life!  Great atmosphere in The Mission.  Come out and ENJOY!!
Creative cocktails, yummy bites, and the Decour is to die for comfortable cozy big hug of a place.

result.reviews.text:
Just ridiculously amazing. Best burrito I've ever had! I don't know how they do it, but there is so much flavor on everything, all crammed into that rather large burrito. And the price was super cheap! The line is long, but it moves fast, and your food is ready before you know it.

Cash only, and normally I would hate that, but everything about that burrito made my life wonderful.

Best burritos in the Mission. Crane Masada Super .Burrito is the way to go. Line can be long but it moves pretty fast, and they only accept cash. Getting a table can be a little tricky at times depending on the time of day. This is the only burrito place in the Mission I go to now.

Over priced mexican food service was a disaster crowded stay away at all cost. I expected better small portions served 14$ for a burrito I know it is sf but come on it is mexican food take it from  a Mexican

super hyped, really crowded, and not all that cheap anymore. the burritos are delicious but guac is actually very non flavorful. super watery salsa. overall i'm going to hustle back to taqueria cancun

We the entire Yellow team visited this restaurant for our afternoon lunch on second day of LGsummit16. I liked mexican dishes, staffs are helpful too. One thing I noticed the restroom was not clean so I am not giving 5 stars rating.

result.adr_address: 3015 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.formatted_address: 3015 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA

result.reviews.text:
This place has rightfully very tasteful plates. I really liked the Peruvian Tamal and the Arroz con Mariscos (seafood and  rice).

Legalmente algo muy bueno y para recomemdar.
The best Peruvian food I ever eat with the real traditional flavor of that country,they using fresh products on every dish, they prepare your dish instantly,I totally recommend.
Amazing flavors, kind service,  prices you can't imagine.  Go here and eat everything!
Best ceviche in town...
Incredible food best chicken and lamb in the Mission.

result.formatted_address: 2893 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA

result.reviews.text: The pupusas were delicious! I would recommend eating there and not taking it to go. Took a little long to get the food and not the friendliest staff but they were pretty busy. It was worth the 15-20 minute wait.

Awful customer service. Very rude.. took about 25 min for 2 pupusas that the cook forgot to make in our order... not even an apology for the delay. We asked to have a drink exchanged, since it tasted like dirty water not Tamarindo and the waiter/owner refused to exchange it.. arguing that  we had already tasted it. Not to mention the $11 she charged for her tip... very disappointing.
Nice simple and cheesy, but they take forever to be made! ..not a quick place for take away. I had good service..
Nice pupusas, but they always seem to take a really long time. Not a place for a quick bit. But the service is friendly!
Very rude costumer service, coming straight from the owner. Not going back to this restaurant ever again.

result.formatted_address: 3150 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA

result.reviews.text: Chopped chicken livers on shmalz griddled Jewish rye with little pickled onions and chopped hard boiled eggs...OMG. SO. GOOD. OTOH had I read the review about dropping the food on the floor first, I doubt I'd have come here. Puts some tarnish on the experience for sure!

Gave a review on Oct 4 seems to have disappeared. Witnessed food dropped on wet floor then prepped for serving (dill) told manager, and he pretended to talk to the worker about it....my skin may be white pero Entiendo español (I understand spanish)....not cool....NOT KOSHER
Everything bagel with salmon blew my mind today. Amazing breakfast when combined with latkes and challah French toast! This is a must visit for brunch or any other meal.

I always wanted to come here but the idea of trying to find parking in the Mission on the weekends kept me away.   I'm glad I did.   I've had their matzo ball soup and pastrami sandwich at the down town location next to the Jewish Museum.   At this location they have fries with pastrami and chipped pickles.  The fries were fresh potatoes.   Yum!
Service is quick and friendly.

Great Jewish deli in the middle of the Mission neighborhood. The pastrama is thick and delicious. They also have babka, which is to die for! It combines nuts and chocolate in a cake that is absolutely delicious. I would recommend this place for a unique meal!

result.formatted_address: 2966 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Hot Press

result.reviews.text: You could walk past this place every day and hardly notice it. It feels like someone's back room, and is about as laid back, which is great. The food was really pretty tasty too. Small and nothing special (vege) but tasty! :)

This place is great, I have tried three of their panini and they all have great flavor. The only thing I can suggest is the tri-tip to be sliced thin instead of chunks and to make sure that there isn't to much fat (most of the tri-tip on mine was fat) and the slice the tomato a little thinner so it's easier to bite.

I would post a photo of my favorite Mozza-licious sandwich, but I'm always focused on devouring this pesto-basil-mozzarella-tomato panini. And I would eat here more than my typical once a week if i wasn't so embarrassing about my gluttonous enjoyment of this simple panini. My  partner really enjoys spicier food so he orders the Ayia Napa (extra spicy!). Plenty of seating, food comes out quick, and there's wifi access. Always check the beverage fridge for the rotating sodas! Chai colas, small batch root beers and tonight- a savory serrano pepper dry soda.

This place is great - they have free WiFi, good coffee (French press!), great paninis (the eggplant one is so good!), Three Twins ice cream, and the guy who works there is super friendly. 

Minus one star only for the ambiance - they have a TV in there and are playing sports or whatever show instead of hipster music. But I don't mind: an undiscovered coffee/sandwich shop is worth it. And I feel like if you had a request they'd change the channel.
This place is amazing and I miss it!!! I recommend to try everything.

result.adr_address: 3146 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110-4012, USA
result.formatted_address: 3146 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Taqueria Guadalajara

result.reviews.text: Really lovely people that work there! $3.10 for a tasty vegetarian taco the size of my whole hand, and almost as tall as it is wide + chips and salsa is amazing value! Tasty too!!

GREAT burritos. The best I've found in the city, actually. They're reliably packed with tasty ingredients in the perfect ratios. The carne asada is a particular standout, though the fantastic fresh tortillas they use are great regardless of what meat you choose. 

The salsa bar is great, with a wide range of options from mild to very spicy depending on how you're feeling (and self service salsas mean you can load up the chips, which you need to as the chips are just average).
Highly recommend! Loved the salsa bar and the food is amazing.
Great burrito, and the salsa was kick ass with just enough spiciness for my taste.
Greatest find in the Mission. I always find my way back here whenever I visit the city as this has become my favorite comfort food destination around the area.

result.adr_address: 3166 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.formatted_address: 3166 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Chili Cha Cha 2

result.reviews.text: Fast service, amazing food, and pretty inexpensive (we went at lunch). I would STRONGLY recommend this place!! Great presentation on the food too!

High quality Thai food, real gem in the mission. So happy I live a few short blocks from it. Green curry beef, tom yum Kai soup, and honey duck are my favorites. 3/4 price of Osha and similarly great presentation and ridiculously good Thai food.
Wow really, beef pad thai, straight food poisoning, hating life right now. Beef pad thai, wtf htf
Three stars for the food. Tasty but average. One more star for the good value $9.95 lunch special
Delicious pad thai, and at a fantastic price. Service here is great, and they do a great job with fast takeout.

result.adr_address: 3126 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.formatted_address: 3126 24th St, San Francisco, CA 94110, USA
result.name: Sun Rise Restaurant

result.reviews.text: Sun Rise is an undiscovered tresoro in the Mission. The owner has high standards for cleanliness and healthy food. She offers a variety of vegetarian and meat pupusas and uses fresh ingredients to serve up pupusas that are not greasy.  She is a humble and hardworking chef whose health-conscious approach to delicious food is born not of any culinary trends but her love of feeding her family in that way. So thankful we by chance stumbled into Alba's restaurant.

Lovely people and a great cosy community feel to it. ..that said, the American style food there is pretty tasteless. Each ingredient was just a little off.. eg the eggs florentine has the eggs cooked hard all the way through, the sauce pretty watery, and the spinach oddly salty. Just all round a little off.

Vegan breakfast burritto was phenomenal, I was really suprised at how delicious it was . Also ordered plantains and they were cooked to perfection . I was beyond satisfied with the food and the staff was very nice .So glad I decided to finally try them out after walking past many times
Came here for vegan French toast. Totally worth it!
"Delicious, absolutely delicious" were the words of my girlfriend after she tried the vegan burrito. Definitely food for the taste not the sight, but with responses like that, does it matter?

result.formatted_address: Pier 7, The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: The Waterfront Restaurant & Cafe

result.reviews.text: I would never go back to this restaurant. We were celebrating two special birthdays in our family,  and the service was horrendous!!  Our waiter said to us just as we sat down  - "What do you want - our kitchen is closing soon."  Very rude!  We felt rushed the entire dinner.  If the restaurant did not want a late reservation, they should not have taken one!!

I shouldnt have sat outside in front by the sidewalk, it was too windy and cold to enjoy the meal. Usually, outside is quieter, but of the times I have eaten there, I have eaten in the back, where it is more sheltered. It is elegant and good service. We have been there at night, as  it is one of the best places to see the light show on the bay bridge.

Food was just awesome! The Ahi tartar just omgosh...green bean with bacon just yummy! Really tastey lots of flavor. 
 Now for the "really" moment... the $$$$ was more like $$$$$$$$$$. The kobe new York strip was like butter once you were able to cut it... ya shouldn't leave tendon maybe a bit more trimming needed.  The Mai Tai I thought Fu fu drink nopes wow there be alcohol no complaints here might need to make sure walk home or Uber driver... lolololol

I had a business dinner at the Waterfront tonight and from the very start the waiter was rude and was noticeably ignoring our table. It took nearly three hours to complete dinner because it was so slow. He was also noticeably being conservative on the wine, as if we could not pay for anything. Also, they were out of at least one dessert. Finally the bill came and I give him my corporate card to pay and he says it is declined... Should have seen that one coming, I told him it was a corporate card and I had to pay with my personal card. We left and I tried my corporate card at another venue and it worked just fine. I do not recommend this place, especially for business dinners where you would like to wine and dine you clients and not embarrass your company.

Rude waiters, 
Forced Tip taking waiters,
NOT RECOMMENDED
only 7 items on menu
FOOD QUALITY TASTELESS

PRICE VERY EXPENSIVE AND THEY SELL U WORTHLESS STUFF
i WOULD TAKE NOTHING ELSE OTHER THAN A FULL REFUND MAILED TO ME...

result.formatted_address: Pier 5, The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: Coqueta

result.reviews.text:
I took my mom here for a fancy birthday lunch and they burnt our paella. When I complained that it was burnt on the bottom, they told me "that's the way paella is made". Umm, no. I'm Spanish. I've eaten paella in Spain. It never comes burnt like that. The rice on the bottom was literally black and inedible. What bothered me the most was how they told me I'm wrong. Who does that? 
They gave us a complementary cheesecake dessert which was honestly absolutely delicious. It's cheesecake made from manchego cheese. Wow. Very good. Will not be coming back though. I dropped 100$ on lunch because I wanted to treat my mom and I was served burnt rice.

This is the 5th times or more in the past 3 years. 

Make reservations. Walk in is hardly likely a good choice.

Food: I think i have tried almost 80% of the menu but still haven't get a chance to try the $80 steak, which requires a large party. Everything on the menu is worth to try out.

Drinks: Their cocktail is so pretty that your ladies will love it.

Mediocre. On the good side: Very beautiful surroundings in the restaurant and well portioned tapas. On the bad side: very noisy and the tables are very close, making it difficult to have privacy. So I would not recommend the place, if you go for a romantic dinner. Moreover, there are only two restrooms for over 100 guests, which means that you have to wait in line. Some of the tapas dishes I do not consider as a real dish. An example is the dish with a small green peppers. One can get the impression that the dishes do not quite fit together. Therefore, I recommend the restaurant that they have a prepared menu, which they can present to the customer.

I've been here twice and it is becoming a one of my favorites! The atmosphere is lovely and the food is delish! The staff is amazing, shout out to Chef, Ryan Patrick, Alex and Ericka!!  They are attentive and really work to know what you would like! Wait!! Did I mention the cocktails? They are beautiful and tasty. If you are looking for a great place to visit with friends or a delicious spot with your person... This is the place! 😄

Coqueta by Chef Michael Chiarello	(means “Flirt” or “Infatuation”  in Spanish) 

The beautiful Embarcardero location with its “Spanish Flair,” a view of the water, the small plates, the gracious staff and the incredible wine list is a must.  Inside, the soaring rustic space is very chic with reclaimed wood, oak table tops, and branded hides on the floors. 

The minute we stepped into the beautifully glass-enclosed entry, we were greeted by Ericka with her very warm and welcoming smile.
Marc Peyer, the Assistant General Manager, was very gracious and helped us maneuver through the tapas menu with his favorite recommendations as well as wine pairings.  
Marc understood our wine preferences and was spot on with his recommendations.
Our waitress, Darnelle, was very efficient, informative and a pleasure to spend the evening with.   A great staff and most enjoyable evening!

Our favorites included:
     Pulpo a la Parilla wood grilled mediterranean octopus,		
     freshly dug fingerling potato, pimentón olive oil $14

     Pintxos Bite-size Skewers (offered tableside) $2.50

     Salmón Ahumado Smoked salmon, queso fresco and 
     truffle honey $8

     Paella, The classic, made with bomba rice, jamón
     serrano-shellfish broth, Gulf shrimp, clams, chorizo with 
     Thumbelina carrots, pickled garlic scapes and lemon alioli,	
     $45 serves 2-3

     Pulpo a la Parilla wood grilled mediterranean octopus,
     freshly dug fingerling potato, pimentón olive oil $14

     “Gaucho” Bistec wood grilled bone-in 32oz natural beef
     ribeye with aromatic Moorish pepper   
     Serves 2-4 $84

      The shrimp and razor clam paella was the best I have 
      had.  Allow approximately 45 minutes for preparation.

       The rice was properly cooked to al dente and the large 
       shrimp and razor clams were in abundance.

        The bone in rib-eye was perfectly carved and just the right
        temperature of rare.  

        The Manchego Cheesecake bites were the perfect sweet-
        salty desert.

         The attention to detail on presentation throughout the meal 
         was a visceral journey.

Recommended food - Super Burger (burger with bacon and a fried egg on top)!
Great bartenders, food, drinks & vibe. Couldn't ask for more.
Great atmosphere and great drinks with tvs for sport
Nice divey pub, with solid beer and pub food. Great place for a quiet weekday lunch!
Really enjoyed Grumpys.  We were from out of town so it was our first and only time there but would recommend to a friend if they were in the area.

result.formatted_address: 150 Broadway, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA

Great place for a warm cup of hot chocolate and tasty sandwiches
Excellent coffee and service. A peaceful area to get some work done. Some good salads and sandwiches for a quick lunch also. Definitely the best coffee in the area.
Love their ice tea and lattes! Staff is very helpful and accommodating

staff is super friendly here, still just a subway
Mostly quick

This is the second time I've tried to get a sandwich and ended up waiting for five minutes while there was no one behind the counter. Left after five minutes of yelling into the back area for someone to come help me.
Nice service

result.adr_address: The Embarcadero #108, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.formatted_address: The Embarcadero #108, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: The Plant Cafe Organic

result.reviews.text: Great location, but the food leaves something to be desired. The ingredients all seems fresh and quality, but the dishes are lacking that flavor that finishes them off. With the number of restaurants around this area, I really can't suggest it.

AVOID! Keep moving to the Market next door. My wife and I were told it was a 10 minute wait, but it was actually 45 mins. The hostess seated others in advance of us and others waiting by mistake. Just a mess and all while many tables were open.  Coffee was served cold. Food was OK , but way over priced for what you got. Had to ask 3 times for coffee and never got jam.  Servers were bickering with each other, I could go on. 

Skip this place. Overpriced, terrible service and food is OK at best.

The food was fine, finding out I'd been charged $50 extra was not. I gave everyone the benefit of the doubt by contacting the restaurant directly when I saw my credit card statement a few days later. The manager took my information and told me she'd get back to me later that day. She didn't.

I called again today a few hours ago, the manager was on another call, then she stepped out. They took my information again and I still haven't heard back. I finally contacted my credit card company to resolve the issue. I've worked in the service industry, it shouldn't be this hard to correct a fairly large mistake that they made, or at least let me know they're working on it.
I visited "The Plant Cafe Organic" for dinner and ordered quinoa bowl w/ chicken and it was delicious and I felt very refreshed after the meal!!!   Definitely looking forward to coming back:))

Delicious healthy food, but plenty of less healthy options if that's not your thing and a good mix of vegetarian and non-vegetarian options. The Plant Burger (signature veggie burger) is definitely a tasty option - even for meat lovers!

result.adr_address: 799 Battery St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.formatted_address: 799 Battery St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: The American Grilled Cheese Kitchen

result.reviews.text: Best grilled cheese I've had. Was slammed at lunch time, but the staff worked hard to get us our food as quickly as they could

Delicious grilled cheese sandwiches, the best lemonade I've ever had (be sure to try their specialty sodas) and even better service! I can't express enough how impressed I am with their employees!  
I only wish they were open later. I rarely get a lunch break so I don't get here as often as I would like.

have probably driven by this place a few hundred times over the past 15 years and FINALLY went for a (casual) business meeting a few weeks ago. Totally awesome. It was Silverlake chill and funky but not high-brow. 
I ordered the fried chicken and absolutely adored it. Good chicken, good. Definitely want to head back for brunch to try the pear pancake I keep hearing about.
Delicious Reuben plus salad. Good vibes, tasty cheese!
FiDi/Jackson Square gets very own TAGCK comfort food done right with delicious grilled cheese sandwiches, soups, and other items

result.reviews.text: The history of this place drew me in as I'm a sucker for that stuff. Worth swinging in for a drink just to say you did it. Service / bartenders were friendly enough. Food was ok for bar food. Can't say anything about the drinks as I was just drinking beer.
Cozy, divey, and close to work - just the way I like it. Pub food, beers on tap, a few screens for sports.
A dive bar. Small and uninteresting. Not my kind of place, what can I say.
This place is OK to watch sports, great service, the Parmesan French fries are awesome!
Nice little place to have drinks after work. Very standard pub with ok priced beer on tap. The Cobb salad was outstanding.

result.reviews.text: As an avid foodie, this place has the best Mediterranean. I came upon them on a walk and loved the lamb and chicken, great location and service. This is a must for everyone.

If you don't mind spending a good amount of money this place is fantastic. The food was superb and our server was even better. He was very attentive and helpful. The atmosphere is great too.  One of the better dining experiences I've ever had.
The wait was long, that's to be expected. The food was delicious and well executed. The decor at the front of the house was charming. Reservations are a must to avoid the wait.
It was good but not for that price. I felt like it was a bit pretentious. Didn't feel like I got what I paid for. Nothing was bad but nothing was worth the price either.
Good place to go, staff has been served us ok, only the price wasn`t what I expected.

result.formatted_address: 465 Davis Ct, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA

result.reviews.text: Very good food, very nice service
Nice French/Russian restaurant. Good food. Good staff.

It was my 80th birthday. the place was empty, and the two waiters were obviously new hires.  They were pleasant, but did not hear very well.

When it was time to order, my wife was told that they were out of her choice.  I was told the same thing for my choice.  It made me think of Restrauant Impossible on the Food Network Channel.

We then had to choose the Filet.  Mine was perfect, but my wife's was still pink.  She asked for welldone.

Sorry to see such a nice place slide.
really pricey but great food
Great food and music

result.reviews.text: Fast and cheap, this is a great quick lunch spot for some decent tariyaki chicken and some gyoza. Nothing fancy, but hits the spot.
cheap good basic japanese food, cash only
Delicious noodle soup at an amazing price. Owners are extremely welcoming.
Interesting little hole in the wall. Not really to my tastes, but it's pretty popular.

I come here once a week for lunch to get their delicious Udon noodle soup. The owners are very nice, their service is super fast, and the food is also cheap! The regulars are always introducing their friends and co-workers to this place.

result.formatted_address: 209 Jackson St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA

result.reviews.text: Downtown SF has it's share of Buffet style salad bar/hot food items, and this is by far the rankest of all of them. I probably should have just walked, but the adventurous spirit in me had to know. The food in the buffet is extremely undesirable. I thought this one item was cole slaw and it was imitation crab. The seating area is extremely drab. The forks they give you are super low quality. All in all, I have very little understanding of how this place stays in business. On a positive note, I felt like I was giving out too many 4 and 5 star reviews, so this takes care of that.
Awesome cafe
Really terrible food

result.adr_address: 244 Jackson St, San Francisco, CA 94111-1826, USA
result.formatted_address: 244 Jackson St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: 5A5 Steak Lounge

result.reviews.text: Terrible "steak house".  The cuts of meat were not quality cuts.  Their cooking perpetration dried out both of our steaks.  They try to hide this with slathering all of their cuts with sauces and glazes.  Service was very slow for only having four other tables occupied.  The wine list is average at best.  Prices were high for the quality of food and service that was received.  I would not consider this a destination restaurant to consider with all of the other options around.

Delicious! I was lucky enough to come here with a group and try a bit of everything. Nothing was disappointing. I loved the prime rib and the wagyu beef was melt in your mouth. I also loved the sweet potato gnocchi side dish and the foie gras on brioche. So much great food, so little stomach space. I will definitely be coming back to try everything again!
Atmosphere was nice and classy.  Food was really good!  They have A5 Wagju beef here which is impressive!  Watched a gentlemen across from us  get their 4 Wagju sampler for $550!!!!
Food was good, but I definitely knows lot of better places in this price range. Staff was not very attentive, sometimes forgetting to ask people for their order, etc.
Great service and AMAZING food! Grab yourself some truffle fries, a filet, and their mashed potatoes!

result.adr_address: Pier 3, The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.formatted_address: Pier 3, The Embarcadero, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.name: Hard Water

result.reviews.text: Great bourbon and American whisky selection. The place was packed with costumed Halloween partiers when we were there, so service was pretty slow, but I'm guessing that's not normal. Very convenient location - halfway between the Ferry Building and the Exploratorium. The Brussel sprouts were very crispy and flavorful. One gotcha: unless otherwise specified, whisky prices are per ounce, but the standard pour is two ounces.
The food is okay. They need to dial the spirit list back down to reality. Not sure who is paying out the nose for those whiskeys, but it's very off-putting.

Good was fine and whisky collection good, but service was genuinely awful. We say at the bar and had to ask to order food, ask for drinks, stack our plates up to be cleared, etc. One of the barmen just wanted nothing to do with us, and the other was spending more time saying how stressed he was and complaining about his waiting team than helping anyone... Really poor experience.

A local friend mentioned that since I like Whiskey I should check this place out. I cannot believe how great an idea that was. I feel like flying back in to SF just to have an evening here with some lovely bourbons.
Nice selection of cocktails, great bourbon, love their bar snacks..got to try their pork crackling..so good.

result.reviews.text: Fantastic food to top off a fantastic experience! The wait staff are professional, ensuring that you're always taken care of. The food is delicious, well worth ordering and sharing bites with friends! The interior is very nice, although the seating can be a bit tight, and the volume can be on the loud side. Be sure to reserve your table, this place is hopping with the after work crowd and those looking for a top notch meal!
Basque food, a personal favorite since childhood. This is my birthday lunch spot!
Delicious hand crafted cocktails. The ox tail is fantastic and so is the fried Manchego.
Great food. Overpriced for the quality though.

We were a group of eight for dinner and thoroughly enjoyed   Dale had reserved and it was fine I had sautéed spinach that was terrific and then a steak that was also terrific everyone enjoyed what they had and it was A nice place

result.adr_address: 924 Sansome St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.formatted_address: 924 Sansome St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: Henry's Hunan

result.reviews.text: Good food and reasonable price. But felt they used little excessive oil and soy sauce.
Quick, affordable and tasty

So I went here with a few friends the other day and I gotta say that the service was the worst I have ever had.  The meat is chewy, has a really gross texture, and noodles are slimy.  A waiter brought out a dish we didn't order and said the rice comes with the meal but then charged us for it and the extra dish we had no idea about.  They are very sneaky and want to trick you into buying things.  We couldn't understand what he was saying.  Also my friend wanted thr frog, pork rice bowl,  but the waiter pretty much wrote him down for a meal that was 5 dollars more b/c we couldn't understand him.  I don't understand why this restaurant is still in business, don't go here unless you can understand the waiter. Really bad service and not so great food.  It would be worth it to go a little farther or get something else to eat.
Stopped in here while doing some work in the city and was very pleased with the food. Family-style portions of delicious food at very reasonable prices. We will definitely return.

Henry's Hunan is some of the best Chinese food I've had in San Francisco, we were not disappointed. The customer service was awesome and the service was top notch, they were friendly and always attentive. What can I say, we'll be back soon!! We ordered Kung Pao Chicken, Fresh sautéed Squid and Dry-sautéed string beans... Everything arrived hot and on time, making our nice evening even better.

result.adr_address: 2257 San Jose Avenue, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.formatted_address: 2257 San Jose Avenue, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Crazy Pepper

result.reviews.text: We're visiting San Francisco from out of town and decided to take the J line to the end and we saw this place. When we came in it was empty which I found slightly odd but the amazing smell coming from the back told me to give it a chance. We weren't disappointed! The food and service were great and we will definitely come back next time we're in town. For reference we ordered the vegetable spring rolls, pork pot stickers, mango chicken and bbq pork with tofu. All amazing!
I like the options they have completed to a traditional Chinese restaurant. Not as authentic as other locations I've been in but at least they have they items on their menu. Will definitely return.

This review is only for their Korean fried chicken. I love how crispy the actual chickens, despite being drenched in this glaze. It's honestly not too spicy nor is it too sweet. The location is right across the street from the Balboa Park station. The actual restaurant from the outside doesn't look like much, but once you go it it looks like a nice sit in place.
Food is just ok, nothing too special. The only thing I recommend would be their lunch special.

I can't get enough of the crab rangoons!

Pretty evenly seasoned/sauced food. Good for delivery, and the location is quaint despite it's opposition the MUNI/BART park. Fantastic people!

The price could stand to come down by 5-10%.

result.formatted_address: 501-, 503 Geneva Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Nina Claire Filipino Restaurant

result.reviews.text: Great, affordable homes type Filipino cuisine. The menudo is aaaamaaazing and the sisig is so good, it's great for taking home and making sisig tacos. Highly recommend you stop by!
Their sisig fries are amazing! I would definitely go there again!

Amazing addition to the neighborhood.  Glad these folks opened up, because the food tastes great and prices are extremely reasonable. 
Great take away too

result.adr_address: 4994 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.formatted_address: 4994 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Kuta Bistro Filipino Cuisine

result.reviews.text:
Seems like they moved the vapor shop to the back or something. Hardly noticed it at all except for the sign on the wall over a table. No smoke no vapor in the dining area at all. So that being said this place was pretty decent. Everyone in my party seemed to like it. I thought it was pretty average filipino fare, nothing outstanding but nothing bad either.
Service was also decent and nice. My quest for the best filipino food in the Bay Area continues.

result.adr_address: 5006 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112-3418, USA
result.formatted_address: 5006 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Little Joe's Pizzeria

result.reviews.text: Hands down, best pizzeria that I've been to. Get it by the slice or even a whole pizza, always worth it. The steak sandwich is one of my favorites,  always made to my liking.  They have a great variety of food and amazing people work there. They definitely have the best pizza crust too, make sure to eat it!

Nice place. The room at the back is decorated very fancy (nice padded booths, sultry red and black wallpaper) which makes it feel more like a '20s speakeasy than a random pizza place. The backs so different than the front it feels a bit hidden and special. 

Onto the food - good cheesy garlic bread, solid pizza which is tasty without being anything special. Decent beer selection. 

Overall a good option for pizza, but I'd rather go to Bravo's just down the road for slightly better food and friendlier vibes.
This place is sooooo good the service amazing friendly the food just to die for the drink love there pitcher !!! Beautiful setting clean. Just two thumb up

Been coming here for years, but noticed that they began to start to lag on their pizza department.   They barely put any tomato sauce on their pizza.  The older lady in the  front gives poor service.   This family owned restaurant needs to be on an episode of Restaurant Nightmares.  Just sayin'

All I can say is WOW. My friend and I split the 9" Little Jo's Pizzeria Pizza (Spinach blended with ricotta and feta, mushrooms, onions, and garlic) and it was more than enough for the both of us. It costs $19.50 and takes about half an hour to make. It is definitely worth the wait.I just want abs....resolutely all the bread in the world. For those who love those crabs as much as I do, you will die with the first bite of your pizza. The crust is SO GOOD... I'm dreaming about it right now. You know your pizza is perfectly baked when it's crunchy and fluffy at the same time. The cheese, tomato sauce, and veggies (topped with chili flakes of course) blend together all so well.The atmosphere and ambiance is perfect for a date. Service is excellent. I will be back!

result.adr_address: 4995 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.formatted_address: 4995 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.name: Maneelap Srimongkoun Restaurant

result.reviews.text: This place serves descent Thai food. It's not great food, but it will pass if you eat there once or twice. BUT don't think you can eat there and have a nice lunch or dinner. The place inside is like an empty hall, high ceilings, with large amount of space in the middle, and it feels really really awkward. As soon as you step in you will understand that you will not want to eat there. And for some reason the floor of the restaurant is very very sticky, which makes you wonder how well they clean the rest of the restaurant and how much they pay attention to the quality of the ingredients they choose to cook with. But after all it's not too expensive. It's not cheap but you'll end up paying $15 per person total, so not too expensive. Yet for that price I'd expect a the food to taste better, and the place to be clean.

The food is really really good. The restaurant is pretty dark. More lighting will make it better. And a brighter and more noticeable sign out front would probably make the place more popular. I passed by the place many times and never noticed it, lol. But I would go back for the delicious food though.

Update 5/15 - I tried to have dinner the other night - table near the door which was wide open onto Mission Street. Outside it was 53F, windy, drizzling. We were told the door had to remain open because it provided the only ventilation in the kitchen. Since we wanted to dine in a restaurant and not a barn, we left. Suggestion - if you want to have a popular restaurant, get the kitchen hood fixed. Seating customers at a table 5 feet from a wide open door in a 55F wind is a horrible way to treat them. I was a regular here, but I'm not going back any time soon...

Previous review: I think this place is great. I usually order from the laotian menu, and ask for recommendations from my server. The people who work here are super nice. One of the best things about this place is that it is a quiet place to have a great dinner. Tables are not packed on top of each other like on Valencia, so you do not need to interact with people at other tables. I've eaten here about a dozen times and it's among my favorite restaurants in SF. Also, this place is way out of the way, good street parking, no one "hip" who rides a commuter bus to work makes it out this far for dinner.
Literally can never pronounce the name, but the owner is the nicest person I've ever met. I love your green curry!

We came here because my mom had some type of coupon deal (not sure if we would have found ourself in the Excelsior otherwise).  The food was tasty and for decent prices, but the experience was a little off.  The layout of the restaurant is really strange, and it feels like a trek to go to the bathroom.  It was a chilly inside.  It's nice to have both Thai and Laotian offerings on the menu, but portion sizes felt inconsistent.  The entrees arrived before appetizers, but the weirdest part is that the rice was not available until the very end of the meal, rending the rice rather useless.

result.formatted_address: 4935 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Aloha BBQ

result.reviews.text: Pretty good Hawaiian BBQ restaurant. The restaurant is very clean; appearing newly remodeled. Food is tasty. Not as greasy as some other Hawaiian-style restaurants.

This place is the worst in delivering. My fiance and i just ordered some food about an hour ago. The driver came to our address to deliver the food so my fiance went outside to pay for the food. The order was $25.43, my fiance gave him $40, meaing the driver was supposed to give my fiance $14.57 back. The driver only gave back $14. The driver called my phone while i am in the house asking me how much is his tip going to be. What hell??! I am not obligated to give a tip if i dont have to. Usually i would, but when he asked so aggressively, hell no! Long story short, the driver demanded a tip, saying he needed a tip. He said that if he did not get a tip, then he would take the food back and put us on their "do not deliver" list. So the driver literally snatched the $14 out of my fiance's hand, threw the $40 in my fiance's face and snatched the food back as well. This place is so ridiculous and they will lose business if they continue to have people like that working for them.

An OK Hawaiian barbeque spot. They are open early for breakfast, which is nice, but my family wanted Portuguese Sausage, and what they got was not what they expected. It was basically a thin slice of Portuguese sausage flavored luncheon meat or something. I had a usual BBQ chicken and chicken katsu, and they were fine. Had better elsewhere, but it was serviceable. Not much of an atmosphere inside, and if I remember right, it was pretty chilly at our table. If you need a quick fix of Hawaiian BBQ and can't go elsewhere, I guess this is fine.
Simply delicious! Come with friends and order family style to get the full experience.  Hawaiian cookies, drinks and food!

result.adr_address: 4919 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112-3415, USA
result.formatted_address: 4919 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Super Star Restaurant

result.reviews.text: It's the best deal in town. Delicious garlic rice, egg, and huge pork chops (get them Hong Kong style - battered and fried), or tasty Tosilog, or Tapsilog (or various fish or sausages, which I've never tried), for $4 a plate? There's a reason this place is always packed. The food still comes out quickly though. Just wish they were open longer hours.
Best meal you can get for under 5 dollars!  Each dish comes with garlic fried rice,  pineapples or tomatoes, and an egg. My personal favorite is the jumbo fried chicken  bomb 💣
Closer to 4, but it's unfair to not give this place a 5 on value. Hk style porkchops are the way to go.

I've been eating at this hole-in-the-wall place on Mission St (near Geneva) since the then-limited silog dishes were under $2, NO KIDDING. The menu has delightfully expanded over the years to include Hongkong-style dishes. Super delicious, huge portions, hot and fast. Take note, my fellow Pinoys--it was actually a Pinoy who introduced Jeff--the amiable owner, then single--to our beloved silog dishes, taught him to cook them to please our palate, and encouraged him to invest in the restaurant. He & his family have come a long, long way, buying houses along the avenue of success. Way to go, Jeff, still amiable and humble through it all!

Its horrible to be hungry and follow the review online to find a good place to eat and find out that this place is unhealthy. The food is very low quality and the worst thing the entire restaurant is so dirty. 
Definitely I'm not going back to  this place.

result.adr_address: 5080 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.formatted_address: 5080 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Rincon Latino

result.reviews.text: All the food here is fantastic! If you're on a diet, surrender your sacrifice to the awesome Salvadorian flavors here. Depending on your personality, the ambiance may not be for everyone. It can get pretty loud during certain soccer, baseball, and football games. If loudness is not your thing, I suggest experiencing this place Mon, Tue, and Thur when it's more family oriented.
The Pupusas are perfect, not greasy and thick.
My favorite salvadorean place
Meat was a bit fatty for my taste, but otherwise very (!) good and friendly staff too.

The prices are more than reasonable and the food is superb! You have to try their $1 Pupusas on Tuesdays. I’m not sure how long they will have this special, but take advantage because the are sooooo good and not greasy like others. They have Menudo, beef, chicken, and seafood soup with handmade tortillas on Fri and Sat. Sooooo good! The only two negative things I have to say is that this place is cash only, so be ready with cash. Also, parking is street/metered parking only, so you may have to walk around the block to find a spot when it’s busy. It’s not a long walk though. Other than that, check this place out!

result.adr_address: 880 Geneva Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.formatted_address: 880 Geneva Ave, San Francisco, CA 94112, USA
result.name: Pho Nice Vietnamese Restaurant

result.reviews.text:
I had been going to Pho Nice on Geneva Blvd in San Francisco for approximately 5 months every week.
I always order the same thing. (Grill Shrimp) over rice. I ask for extra sauce.
Yesterday I went in,  I waited 15 minutes before a kid came from the back area and saw me and told someone I was standing at the desk. A lady who I never saw before, THE MEAN LADY came to take my order ,and I was asked to pay before I got my order. I told her I have always paid after my order was ready. When the order was ready, the same lady who I never saw before gave me a different price from I have paid previously .
 I asked if the price had changed ? she replied, yes a few months ago. I said I have been buying for 4 months and the price was always the same. I told her I was just here a few days ago. She turned around talked in her Vietnamese language to everyone working in the restaurant including the customers. She turned back to me and told me the extra charge was for the extra sauce I asked for. I asked her why now charge me for the extra sauce when they never did before.
At this time one of the young lady's who had help before came out, as well as a young man who had helped me before. The first ( evil) women  said (they said they gave you the sauce for free because you were a  great customer who comes in all the time). SHE THEN SAID ( I AM NOT MY SISTER, I AM FROM THE CORPORATE OFFICE AND YOU MUST PAY. I paid it, everyone in the restaurant was looking at me.
It was only $1.00 more. I did not have a problem paying a dollar more and I had always gave a $2 dollar up to $5.00 tip..I have purchased up to 4 dinners at a time, If four people had come in to eat at the table and asked for extra sauce, would the (evil one) come out and say. YOU PAY MORE ?. I don't think so.
This so call women from  (Corporate office) was rude and unprofessional, she need training from her sister and everyone else in the restaurant . I do not speak in a loud tone, I am also in the food service business, I would not risk loosing a great customer who comes every week and insult her for a 1/2 once of sauce. I have always given a tip even though it was always take out.
This restaurant would do better if this ( so call women from the corporate office were not around). She needs to go back to Corporate Office. She must be a family member with power and no business training on how to keep good customers.
I will not be  back.

The price is good, been coming here for years but disappointed that the pho I had today lacked tripe (meh) and tendon (darnit) and the sides were missing sprouts and mint leaves. 

Idk, would be nice to be notified about that but still not a bad place overall
From out of town and this was a random find from a Google search. The  imperial rolls and rare steak pho was excellent. Everyone enjoyed their lunch and we were easily able to fit our group of 7.

North Vietnamese style.
Therefore, its not your typical pho place.

Pho Nice took over a previous Pho place and I'm super glad. They had totally bad customer service. Anyway, here the customer service is great! The workers here don't speak much English so that can be a problem. They are also very reserved and timid. 

Regular Pho - Different type of noodles. The noodles are flat. The broth is much more different than the "south Vietnamese" type of broth. What is odd about this place is that they don't serve condiments such as cilantro and lemon like all typical pho places.

Hai Noi Bun is pretty much on point. The lettuce is fresh and the noodles are cooked to perfection. They also gave an abundance of meat. The presentation was also beautiful. 

Bun Bo Hue (emphasis on the hue, you vietnamese people would probably get the joke) - Broth is super sweet. A bit too much oil in the broth. After a few sips of the broth, I grew to like the sweetness of the soup. 

Definitely will be coming back when I'm craving for northern Vietnamese style pho and dishes because has great service and a clean place.
Love the rare steak pho and I always get their papaya salad. My favorite local pho place.

Get the chicken andouille

Absolutely the best corn dog I have ever eaten. There is a multitude of delicious meats to choose from, with the option of even creating and mixing a 3 meat corn dog. The batter is to die for and I highly recommend you to go to Batter Up right now :)
batter up has the best corn dogs. The price is very goood. the sauges dogs are great to.

All in all, this will definitely be my go-to Chinese food spot since I live close by and the food is really not bad at all.

result.reviews.text: Love, this place. Atmosphere is great. It can get crowded real quick, but well worth the wait. Staff are good and always friendly. Cant beat the all you can eat Sushi plus drinks for adults and kids. Other wise, their menu has a lot to choose from. If you drive, good luck because its hard to find parking, most of the time. 😀🍱🍣🍜
We went for bottomless sushi and drinks. The service was fast and the sushi was great. I would definitely come here again.

Pretty good sushi for AYCE. Would definitely avoid the rush if you want to get the most bang for your buck.

My favorites were the DJ roll, sunrise and oysters.
It was ok. The tonkatsu was bland and the salad dressing didn't taste authentic. The beef there is so good so tender, but the sauce.. it was overall ok...

Great variety of rolls, sashimi and nigiri. They ran out of the live uni during my visit but the live scallop was delicious and sweet. They even cook the small mussels from the shell and deep fry it into a second dish which was pretty cool. Wild hamachi, ocean trout and uni nigiri were all favorites! 

Great place to go if you want to eat some good quality fish without having to break the bank. The restaurant is on the smaller side so make reservations ahead of time. Servers were friendly and very efficient!

result.reviews.text:
One the best pizza I've had!
I got a XL #1 famous Bravo and 8 pcs hot wings with ranch sauce, and it costs me about $40. But trust me, worth every penny.

The pizza's fresh, hand-made as soon as you order. The pizza dough is hot when it's served but not crispy but soft and delicious.  Wings are hot and just perfect to me personally, with the sweet from the ranch, it's perfect out of perfect.
And not to mention, the floor and owner are all in good attitude to customers.

Worst pizza I have ever had! Don't get fooled with the positive reviews it's fake!!. I ordered pizza 2 days ago from Bravo and it was very dry and old (obviously it was recycled). It cost me 52$+.. ?? After I called them to let them know about the quality of the food, without any care they just told me it's Ok we just lost a customer!!! Think again if you want to order from this Resturant. Worst quality ever and service. This is my honest review and opinion.

Their menu says 'Old School' and that really sums this place up perfectly to me. Pizzas are huge and loaded with cheese. Pastas and other mains are simple but tasty with huge portions. Friendly servers have been there for years. Cheap beer ($10 pitchers!). Just a great old school place!
Awesome or better yet best pizza ever!!! Also the entree portions are huge one plate could probably feed 5!! Great place!
I've coming here since before high school"'81";and it has been true to the code pizza always the same yummy and now my kids and my kids kids come here luv it

result.reviews.text:
As others have mentioned, storefront and inside decor hasn't been updated in decades. So looking at it from the street you may easily pass by it. 

If you're brave enough to stroll in and try it though, you'll be shocked by how good the food is. Chef and rest of service team are really kind and courteous as well. 

Everything on the menu is great and comes in large portions. Expect to take some home unless you're famished. Prices are rock bottom too!

One of my favorite places in the city. The décor looks like it hasn't been updated since the 60s, which makes it kind of glorious. The dinner plates are huge and comforting and actually taste really good. The chicken dinner is only $8, with grilled bread and potato and salad (pro tip, get you dressing on the side if you don't want it drowned). The steaks aren't expensive either. Just all round a fun experience, and really tasty food to boot.
Great food, great place. Everything is beyond awesome. Natives only. Transplants need not enter. Your presence will only serve fo diminish the quality and sanctity of a S.F. gem.

The place needs A make over but the food and service is a 5 star. Great place to get a steak sandwich and a salad and you will love the potato. We should start a gofund me account and update the carpet and tables, this place must remain open for years to come. I live in Antioch and travel to the City just to eat.

result.adr_address: 579 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.formatted_address: 579 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

result.reviews.text:
What We Ordered
- Small Cioppino
- Small Steamed Clams
- Garlic Bread Half Order

I've read reviews about how good the food was and how long the line always is. I had to check it out for myself. I was super disappointed with the cioppino. The seafood in it was NOT FRESH. You could taste it... the weird fishiness. The steamed clams were amazing though! The broth was more of a lemon butter garlic galore. The garlic bread was perfect for dipping...although it was more burnt than necessary. Really torn and probably will not be returning for a second visit.

The Ciopinno is a must have whether in Crab Season or not!  Pair with a glass of Malbec and enjoy.  Sit at the counter.as that is where the action is.  Every time we go there we make new acquaintances and have a blast.  Yes, it is small so, get there early or be prepared for a ,well worth it, wait.  AOB is a true SF jewel..

A Castro institution.
Small, not fancy, informal friendly place with great food reasonably priced.
Reservations  required for dinner.
Was recommended by our AIrBnb hosts as a must do dinner spot.
The Ciopino ( fish and Shellfish Stew ) is to die for but a very large helping.
I ate it all and loved it.
Like many  of the good restaurants the service was surprisingly good and reminded me of the waiters in Montreal.

Hands down the best cioppino! Not even listed on the menu, but mind-blowing. All entree portions are enormous, my neighbor got the shrimp pasta and it could feed four people. Seafood cooked to perfection. I cannot wait to go back!

It's extremely small and had to wait outside in the cold for 45 minutes, shivering. Almost gave up a few times, but was so worth it. Wait staff and owner are so nice.

Only reason not more stars is atmosphere and wait in cold.

This small restaurant in Castro is really really good! It's quite small so we had to wait an hour to get in (you need to sign up on a board by the entrance) but it totally worths waiting. The seafood was fresh and tasty. I suggest also to take 'cioppino', I'll not try to describe it because it's too difficult but I'm still having dreams of it!

result.adr_address: 564 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114-2512, USA
result.formatted_address: 564 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.name: Castro Tarts

result.reviews.text:
This place is consistently good and the owners are super friendly/nice. We used to pass by thinking it was just a Vietnamese sandwich shop (my fiance doesn't like sandwiches for some unbeknownst reason). 

After we realized that there were other foods, we started coming in often during the weekends for brunch (french toast, omelette with avocado and cheddar) which are amazing deals and always delicious. The omelette comes as a set with a pastry (croissant), coffee, and hash browns. Both the french toast + omelette brunch sets will run you below $20. It's probably the most affordable breakfast place in the Castro, while simultaneously being one of the higher quality places. 

As for the non-breakfast items, I can't review the sandwiches but we have also tried their potstickers, which come as a giant serving and are delicious.

The food at Castro Tarts is tasty, and the cost is below average. On top of that, everyone works here is very friendly, I've never had any bad experience. I strongly recommend this place if you are looking for some good eats in the Castro.
A hole-in-the-wall Vietnamese place with great food. But more than that, the people are amazing - friendly, with great service!
Great lemongrass chicken ban mi

A not-so-hidden gem on Castro Street between 18th & 19th. The colorful decor is really adorable, kind of like if the college aged you shared an apartment with your grandmother. Love it! The Vietnamese pastry offerings are tasty and reasonably priced.

result.adr_address: 558 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.formatted_address: 558 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

result.reviews.text: Great food and a very pleasant staff. I had the ribeye and it came with fries. Everything was very well cooked and flavorful. Would highly recommend.

Came here for brunch with some friends. I ordered the chicken sandwich with slaw. It was delicious. Our friends got the French toast and said it was great. Easy to find parking and not overly crowded for brunch.
Great atmosphere.  The outdoor heated patio is awesome.  Food was fantastic.  All four of us liked it a lot.
Took longer than expected to get a table, but good food and a beautiful patio area.

Seems to be reasonably priced and popular in the neighborhood. I'm not a big Sushi eater, but I enjoyed my meal and had a lot of fun. Not sure what I was eating but I tried everything and found it all delicious :-)
Awesome rolls. If you want an "everything bagel" toll that Jackie suggested. Order the Phillips Roll with green onions and lots of sesame seeds.

Nice wait staff and the food is good. Standard pricing for the area and the atmosphere is pleasant.  The bacon wrapped scallops are very good and I was very happy with everything I have tried there so far.  I've had lunch there about 8 or 9 times now and I recommend it as a nice place for sushi.
Very yummy, fingerlicking good sushi. One of the best sushi restaurants ever

result.adr_address: 517 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.formatted_address: 517 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

result.reviews.text: Everything served my table was delicious.  At 8:20 on Thursday night, there was no waiting.  Waiter was friendly and food didn't take long.  Eggplant parmesan was really good.  My friends said this place is reliably good.
Fun joint, great Italian food and friendly service. The decor is very busy, but comfortable and fun
How do you not go to a place called the Sausage Factory in the Castro? I've only had pizza here and it's good. Eventually I'll try the pasta.

I cringe every time I walk past this place. We used to live near The Sausage Factory and I was so excited to try it. We finally did - and the ravioli was really tasteless. To top it off, the wine is poured into the typical hexagonal/round cups used for water (can't remember if it was plastic or glass but it definitely didn't help the taste of the wine). Only positive was that the portions are legitimately big.
It's a great place for awesome comfort food just like mama used to make!

best pizza in castro

Fried corn thing delicious. Duck curry, amazing. Other stuff, less great.

Placed an order online only to find out the restaurant doesn't have a working internet connection.  Staff couldn't tell me how to cancle my order and couldn't accept a credit card.  Disappointed.  Went to thaihouse express instead.

Constantly "OK" in terms of food. Service is usually pretty good. Prices are a bit high for quality of the food. Beer & adult beverages are pricey. Best things on the menu are the Harvey's Messy Skillet (breakfast) and the fried chicken (dinner time).

result.reviews.text: This place is extremely consistent at keeping me fed and happy after a night out. They get points for being clean, cheap, and taking credit cards! Bonus: there's a bathroom behind the kitchen.
Good veggie pizza, tone of topping he on top, has all the veggies compare to other pizza places which is always missing one or the other.
Low keyi best pizza in San Francisco
Great spot for a quick slice, especially late night.

They serve a very solid piece of pizza, but your odds of getting a clean table or smiling face are low. I like their pre-made pizza options that are ready if you want to grab a quick slice and it's awesome that the price is so low. As long as you're not looking for a place to sit down and spend some time with friends, this is a decent option.

result.adr_address: 4243 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.formatted_address: 4243 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

result.reviews.text: Betty, Trevor Mei Mei and all the staff are attentive and considerate. They remember your name and what you like.  Try the Bruce roll. Make sure to ask them for bacon with it, although they will never let you have it ;-)
Best sushi I have ever had! For some reason this place isn't packed all the time. Great atmosphere.
Good spot for fish. Nice selection, festive service, and fresh

Takara is one of our go to place for Sushi in the city. They have one of the best happy hours as well. The food is all reasonably priced compared to other sushi places in the city. The place is small and only has a handful of tables.
Great sushi place and great service.

result.adr_address: 4063 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94114-2535, USA
result.formatted_address: 4063 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA
result.name: Eureka Restaurant & Lounge

result.reviews.text: The chicken was good the other night and I've had the burger in the past it was pretty good. Personally I come here because it's one of the few places in the Castro that can make a decent martini :-)
Great drinks and better service.  Steven is an incredible bartender.  Food is delicious and happy hour prices can't be beat.
Great drinks, dinner, and desserts. Great place for meeting old friends and new. Extremely attentive service. What a lovely and fun evening.

We stayed a few days in Castro on a west coast holiday from London. Was recommended Eureka by the bar man in twin peaks, and what a good recommendation it was. The restaurant and upstairs bar was busy but the host managed to find us a table. I had the spicy jambalaya and she had the meatloaf with mash and veg. Both were delicious.   We had a lovely relaxed evening, shame we weren't staying longer as we would have been back.
One of the happiest Happy Hours you'll find in the Castro.  Full menu in the lounge is a bonus.

result.formatted_address: 4150 18th St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

Stunningly simple, truly flavorsome Mexican food.  Just do yourself the favor.  Visit!!
Pretty good grilled chicken super burrito. Decent Tilapia burrito. Grilled steak burrito was just ok. Salsa bar needs more options.

Good quality for scoop Mexican food. Very popular place in San FRancisc's CAstro district. I recommend keeping it simple here. NOthing that requires melting cheese or an oven. Order the grilled chicken tacos or a simple burrito. There are no shortage of taco places in the Castro. Try Zapata for yourself, then move on to one other 20 choices.
Love this place. Great spot for quick Mexican!

result.formatted_address: 499 Castro St, San Francisco, CA 94114, USA

The food here is neither bad nor great.  Simply okay.

tried the falafel gyro. super tasty will go back to try more.

my favorite place for TREAT YO SELF day. two words marshmallow sauce.  :P

They really nailed the banana flavor! It's like you're squeezing a cold banana... No disgusting artificial banana flavors here! 

Not a lot of flavors to choose from, but they all taste really good. Small place not much seating outside but it's fun to stand outside and watch people stumbling their way on Castro.

This is some of the best frozen yogurt I've ever had, and I'm a big fan of froyo. The flavors I've enjoyed have been the pumpkin and the cocoa-cayenne. That you have to get your sample cups from servers is annoying at best,  they do their best to be friendly about it. The selection of toppings for self-service is broad, and many items are locally made. The price point is a little higher than competition, but the quality is better, too.
Cherry marzipan frozen yogurt made with cashew milk.

This is a great place when you're craving for a nice roast chicken or a plate of pasta. Very good service and prices

Good lunch in a friendly atmosphere. 
Portions are huge!
Followed some local softball players in this place. Figured they know where to eat. Got a pizza with my sweetie. Great atmosphere...great pizza.  Cracker thin crust and just enough.  Ah-ma-zing!!!

result.reviews.text: I got a burrito to dine in. This guy was getting to go and a $20 bill dropped from his pocket while paying. The cook saw he dropped it put his foot over the $20 bill and dragged it out of sight. I called him out and the cook ran to the back and the oblivious guy that dropped the $20 was confused and I explained and he saw it around the bend and picked it up. They are dishonest and literally steal cash from customers. Don't ever come here. If they're that dishonest and steal cash, I can't imagine the integrity that goes into making the food. I actually got sick to my stomach at seeing this and couldn't finish eating.
The worse conbinacion between bad food and horrible costumers service.  I found a cucarach on my plate

I went to this place 2 weeks ago. And really damn near died. Im allergic to shrimp. No questions ask.. We sit down, the food comes. Yes, ready to eat.. I told them, please don't cook, or use the same utensils, as u would use for shrimp. Thank you.. I take two bites and the second one was deadly. I passed out on the floor, forming at mouth because, I stop breathing. I couldn't get up or even take a breath. My friend, ran across the street to Walgreens. ( thank GOD, for them). They gave him an EpiPen. He came back. Hit me with it and I finally I regain my breathing back. EMS was called, and said, "if it wasn't for my friends quick reaction, I may not be here today. Im telling folks more now today, because with cross containing of the food. Can easily take a life.

The taste of WET PAPER TOWEL. Warm service, with a smile. The food?  Disgustingly bland. Forget the lack of any suggestion of spices or condiment on any of their meats... the washout extends to the rice, the beans. It seems there's a concerted effort for everything to taste like a wet paper towel.
I had a grilled shrimp burrito, while friends ordered a ‘mole’ burrito, a chicken burrito, and a steak burrito.  I asked to have a taste of it all…uugh.  This is the worst taqueria food I have tasted in 40 years of splitting time between Cali and Mexico.
You’ll notice a basket of salt packet by the cashier. Apparently the cooks are also allergic to salt and must keep it sealed and at a distance.

Food is decent, though it's not the best Mexican cuisine I've had in the city. Prices are average. Be careful if you're going drunk, as they'll likely give you the higher priced variant of a specific item you request.

result.adr_address: 2101 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94115, USA
result.formatted_address: 2101 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94115, USA
result.name: Sweet Maple

result.reviews.text: Service is quick and food portions are filling. The vibes are good. Great place for brunch. The Marnier French Toast are a slice of paradise. Tell them I sent you 😉

What I Ordered
- Millionaire's Melt with Potato Medley

Come here if you want to feel like your heart is clogging up with oily goodness. My heart hurt while eating the millionaire's melt. It was sweet, savory, and juicy all at the same time. I can see why the wait is so long all the time. I didn't like the arugula in the melt though. It's not easy to bite through in one bite. It just gets pulled out and ends up flicking oil on your face. I'm sure it gave me pimples the next day lol. The potato medley helped cut out the overload of fat but, it's still potatoes so that's not good for you either haha. I will be back if I'm ever in town again. It's super sweet that they offer coffee while you wait. It's super cold in SF so anything will help!
One of the best brunches ever! Millionaires Bacon lives up to it's hype and so does the Big Hip French toast. South of the border scramble was amazing too. Very kids friendly staff! Loved it!

The long wait was definitely worth it. As per other people's recommendations, I ordered Blackstone Benedict. The portion was big and the millionaire's bacon had a pretty interesting taste (sweet taste for bacon). I liked it a lot!

Its ok, went here with a group of friends tried almost everything and altho it was exceptable the wait and the prices were not.
It was also so noisy that we had to have the waitress constently repeat herself. I thought this might be the only place in SF to get millionairs bacon but i was wrong appearently i think these guys have a sister location at the Kitchen Story. Just like this place it has millionairs bacon and waaaay over priced food. The only saving grace for this place is that the sister location actually charges more if you can believe it.

nice for lunch, everything is good here

can get a bit crowded though if you come at the wrong time.

Best neighborhood Thai restaurant I've eaten in. Nee, the owner chef is extremely talented and her presentations of contemporary and traditional Thai dishes is extraordinary. It's a destination Thai food restaurant.
Good Thai food. Didn't get blown away tho. No peanuts with my pad thai.

result.reviews.text: nice coffee, full flavoured, fresh beans.  Very clean, staff are friendly and the atmosphere is relaxed.  Great place to rejuvenate and get caffeinated up!
Good place to grab a latte it a quick cup of coffee. It's a fairly unassuming place. Not a lot of seating available if you want to lounge around for awhile.

Great little coffee shop. Good coffee, service, and atmosphere, along with decent seating. Most people in the shop are working on their laptops, so finding seating can be a hit or a miss depending on the time you go.
Delicious bagel sandwich- Bagel with Veggies- and good coffee too!

Just moved to the area and this is already becoming a favorite neighborhood spot for when I need to work or read. It's cozy and has a nice ambiance. I always enjoy the background music and the staff is friendly. Food is pretty good and I really like their chai mocha. And the wifi is a huge plus- I've found free wifi can be hard to come by in SF! Don't have anything negative to say about this place.

result.reviews.text: The first time I've ever heard or seen? THE BEST TASTE I'VE EVER HAD I'M from Michigan an we have Big Johns steak an onion this just put it to SHAME  THANKYOU SANFRANCISO  CHEESE  STEAK  SHOP 10 STAR'S.

Was there practically every single day waaay back in 1990. They were the best then and probably the only Philly house at that time. Man how I wish sometimes I still lived there and just to go there and Fisherman's Wharf, and ride to Berkeley. Berkeley reminded me a lot of the French Quarter.

I've been to Philly and tried the big two and I still prefer this place. Great cheese steak sandwiches without the attitude and fake cheese whiz😛

result.formatted_address: 1750 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94115, USA

result.reviews.text:
I spent my late lunch here was was very content with my food. The menu was what you expected of a pub, and it wasn't crowded with meaningless items like so many other places. I ordered the special for $9 with consisted of half a sandwich and a side of fries, note that the coke was extra, but that wasn't anything to worry about.

My rueben sandwich was very satisfying with a good amount of melted cheese and savory pastrami. I only wish that the sauerkraut was a little more lively. However, the service was quick and friendly, although it was past the lunch rush. 

Definitely worth a visit again to try their other options.

Really like the food here. A sports bar, with lots of TVs. Full bar, with some tasty specialty cocktails. They do get the big fights /MMA events here, with the usual cover charge. You can come with a group, but you'd better get here early. I'm sure it fills up fast.
Good beer selection, pretty good food for a bar, and plenty of TV's covering all the games. Gets super packed for the big ones though, and more trouble than it's worth.
Such a great place!!!! Crowded, but such good energy!  Delicious food and good drinks.

Terrific sports bar. Tons of big screens and a pretty cool back area with bleachers and large booths. Other novelties include the ability to get a bathtub full of beer (they roll a vintage bathtub full of ice out to your table and fill it with bottles of beer). Good food as well!

result.reviews.text:
I was hungry and I wanted to eat and this place was next door to where we were hanging out at so we went inside and they weren’t open yet! I waited though because at that point I knew I wanted a Unagi Donburi (rice bowl with eel), and they were nice enough to at least give us water while we waited.

When I got the Unagi Donburi, I was a little sad. It was a lot smaller than I thought it would be. On the flip side, it was really good. The rice was warm, sticky and delicious and the eel was really good and I liked the seaweed as well.

Overall, it was really good, but it was more of a large snack than a meal. I know if that’s the case for other items on the menu, but any additions would have totally stacked up the bill.

The best part about this place was the price point. Most basic rolls were $6, and the specialty rolls were around $12. They also serve beer and sake, and have a couple of TVs for sports fanatics or overflow traffic from SFAC.
Great lunch specials. Not the best sushi in town, but a great deal for the price. Very fast, friendly service.

I LOVE GODZILA. These people and the sushi are the best.
Good price for amaze balls sushi. My favorite sushi place ever.
Fresh, tasty, inexpensive, consistent. Amazing lunch specials, fast and friendly service. My favorite go to!!

result.reviews.text: Ordered the BBQ pork bun, pickled cabbage, and Kung Pao Chicken.  The first two were actually unique and pretty good.  The Kung Pao Chicken was disgusting, completely disgusting.  The "so-called" chicken was soft and totally weird.  It had ZERO chicken characteristics.  I told the waitress I didn't believe it was chicken.  Totally gross and hope I don't get sick.  I seriously question all the good reviews.  I should have taken the hint when NO ONE was in the restaurant at 5:30pm.
No frills chinese place, but the service is good, the portions are big, and the food is excellent quality. Prices are good by SF standards.

My wife wanted some Sweet and Sour chicken after delivering our daughter at the Kaiser down the street. This place did not disappoint! Quickly prepared and served hot. We'll be very happy to order from this place again. Well priced and clean environment too.
Pretty good
They are among the best in preparing artificial "chicken" dishes in the city.  Most other Chinese restaurants just use tofu, which is too soft and bland.

BURRITOS THE SIZE OF YOUR HEAD!!!!

Wow, these things are huge.  I recommend the Colorado Beef Expresso.   Tasty.  And with that enchilada sauce topping...mmmmmm.   It's ranked among the top 20 taquerias in SF.  Highly recommended.

The food is very good, I'd say reasonably priced considering how quickly your food comes up and how good it tastes. Burritos also include chips and salsa so it's fair. The service I could pass on, the cashier was not at all interested in being there. At least the burrito was fantastic.

Great hole in the wall Authentic Mexican food. Its in my hood, and I hop over there at least every other week. My only knock would be that its overpriced.. you can get the same in the Mission for $5 less, but hey, this IS Pacific Heights we are talking about :)
Bistec ranchero and cheeseburgers are delicious. Very friendly service.

I was in a rush so today I decided to order to go. Something I consider very convenient. I've been craving chicken fries for a while so today I knew would be perfect to go and grab them. Anywho so I called and placed my order. The lady who answered the phone didn't sound phone trained nor inviting, almost changing my mind or rather or not to continue to place my order. Before I went out my way to travel in the direction of the place to then satisfy my hunger that still isn't getting met. Disappointed customer due to lack of communication

result.formatted_address: 1661 Divisadero St, San Francisco, CA 94115, USA
